title: spicy cucumbers
directions: Peel and cut cucumbers into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat vinegar, oil, salt and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumber cubes and sprinkle with red chili flakes and black sesame seed. Serve cold.

title: cocomoka cold
directions: Pour the chilled coffee into a large, chilled bowl.
Add 1/2 of the ice cream.
Beat until the ice cream is partially melted. Add rum, almond extract and whipped cream.
Fold in the remainder of the ice cream.
Pour into tall glasses and sprinkle with freshly grated nutmeg or grated sweet chocolate.

title: depression carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil and flour two 9 x 1/2-inch round pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except raisins and nuts, at low speed until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter evenly into prepared pans. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake feels firm when touched lightly. Cool completely.

title: skillet chicken divan
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in a large skillet until browned.
Add water, cooking wine, broccoli and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork and sprinkle with cheese.
This recipe makes 4 servings, but it can be doubled.

title: diabetic apricot angel dessert
directions: Place the cake cubes in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 dish; top with apricots. In a saucepan, combine Splenda, cornstarch and apricot nectar until smooth. Bring to a boil; cook and stir until thickened. Remove from the heat. Stir in gelatin until dissolved. Pour over cake and apricots. Cover and chill for 3 hours or until gelatin is set. Spread with whipped topping. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except onion rings.
Pour into cooking dish.
Cook until bubbly, then add onion rings on top. Bake until brown (10 minutes) at 350°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening until size of peas.
Add egg, vinegar and water which have been blended together. Mix just enough to blend ingredients.
The dough will be quite moist.
Roll out as other pie dough.
Makes 2 double crust pies. Bake at 400°.
This crust will keep for 6 weeks in refrigerator if kept well covered.

title: new york style cheesecake
directions: Blend cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter; line bottom of 8 or 9-inch ungreased spring-form pan.
Blend sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla in food blender for 1 minute.
Add cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Pour into pan. Bake in lower third of a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
When baking is finished, remove from oven and turn oven on to broil.
Broil cheesecake just until top begins to show attractive brown spots. Refrigerate for 4 hours, preferably overnight, before cutting and serving.

title: pilgrim pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 10 minutes on 450° then 30 minutes for 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli approximately 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and eggs.
Add broccoli.
Put in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Best to prepare a day ahead and bake just before serving.
Do not add crumbs until time to bake.
Serves 8.

title: pot pie
directions: Layer one crust in pie pan.
Pour in soup, milk, thyme and pepper to taste.
Add vegetables.
Top with pie crust.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add seasoning, tomato sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Mix well. Spoon into casserole dish, 1/2 of meat mixture.
On top of this, layer Ricotta cheese.
Layer remaining meat mixture.
Blend last 5 ingredients in blender for 15 seconds.
Pour over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9-inch, or 2 round, or paper-lined cupcake tins.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour into pan(s). Bake oblong pan 60 to 65 minutes and layers for 50 to 55 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost.

title: ground meat (beef) casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in cooking oil.
Add onion and pepper; cook until almost done.
Add corn
and tomato paste.
Mix with noodles which have been prepared according to directions on package.
Season with salt, pepper, sugar and chili powder to taste.
Pour into casserole baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter s'mores
directions: Place 1 peanut butter cup on each of 4 crackers.
Spear marshmallows on long fork and toast.
Place marshmallow on top of each peanut butter cup and top with other crackers.
Press together for a few seconds to melt chocolate.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 2 hours.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread over baked crust. Combine instant pudding and milk.
Mix until thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until mixed.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Mixture may be refrigerated for about 6 weeks and used when needed.

title: beet cake
directions: Mix thoroughly in order.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Glaze while warm.

title: jessica's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, together. Use 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese for topping.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper to taste.
When browned, drain and add Ragu.
Heat well and simmer.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Use 2 qt. casserole dish.
Begin with layer of ground beef mixture on bottom of dish.
Next layer with macaroni, then 1/2 of remaining meat mixture.
Use 1/2 of sour cream on ground beef and spread out.
Place 1/2 of mozzarella cheese on casserole.
Layer again the same way. Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly hot and cheese is melted.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Cook in iron skillet until thick.
Add coconut, oleo and flavoring.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and sprinkle with coconut.
Brown.

title: mom's cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending thoroughly.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling.

title: rice casserole
directions: In skillet, saute mushrooms and raw rice in oleo for about 5 minutes or until slightly browned.
Add onion soup and 1/4 can water.
Stir and cover.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tangier island corn pudding
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of the milk, then mix in the remainder of milk.
Add corn, sugar and eggs.
Pour into 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch greased baking dish and spoon melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until brown on top.

title: baked apple squares
directions: In a large bowl, beat together sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add oil and vanilla; mix.
Fold in walnuts (pecans) and apples.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger and potato pie
directions: Saute onion in butter; add beef and brown well.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Combine potatoes, egg yolk and melted butter.
Beat until fluffy. Spread over meat mixture in casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: steak and onions
directions: Cut meat on bias into 1/3-inch thick strips.
Pound meat on both sides.
Using knife, stretch meat strips into oblong shapes. Coat with flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in hot butter on both sides until golden brown.
Saute sliced onions in butter.
Place meat in a heavy saucepan and cover with sliced onions.
Top the onions with sour cream.
Pour beef broth over the ingredients.
Simmer, covered, until meat is tender.
If desired, add 1 tablespoon of flour to thicken the sauce.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash, green bell pepper, green chilies and onion until tender (can microwave); drain well.
Beat eggs; add to vegetables with mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: drop sour milk cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Spoon by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375°
for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix together sweetened milk, coconut and flavorings.
Drop by tablespoon onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 10 minutes.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) and put in a cold oven.
Turn oven to 300° and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until firm in the middle.
Let cool completely.
Makes a 3 pound loaf.

title: sweet and sour carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until fork-tender and cool.
Add the other ingredients and chill overnight.

title: crazy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Blend in cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Layer in cake pan, cookies, filling and then cookies again. Make top layer of cookies thick.
Place gummy worms on top for a special treat for kids.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Do not chop nuts; everything is whole. Add remaining ingredients; mix by hand.
Fill greased and floured bread pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours; test for doneness.

title: brownie mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and cocoa. Add eggs and vanilla.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
This makes 3 (8 x 8-inch) pans of brownies.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix Bisquick and margarine in a 9 or 10 inch pie plate. Sprinkle with the boiling water.
Press together, lining the pie plate.
Flute the edges.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes (until golden brown in color).
Set aside to cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add baking powder.
Melt margarine in milk and add to ingredients.
Beat eggs until light and add vanilla and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Add chopped onion, green pepper, grated cheese and bacon bits.
Add sugar and enough mayonnaise to coat cauliflower as desired.

title: sausage and potatoes
directions: Brown sausage; add onion and garlic to saute. Add potatoes and cover with water. Cook on low until potatoes are done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and milk.
Add melted butter and bananas; mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion spice cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and egg; beat well.
Add sour milk in which soda has been dissolved.
Last, add flour, spices, baking powder and salt, mixed together.
Raisins or nuts may be added.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: olive balls
directions: Drain and dry olives. Wrap olives in layer of cream cheese. Place finely chopped pecans in Ziploc bag. Drop olives and cream cheese in pecans and shake until covered. Chill until time to serve. Slice in half and serve.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except shoestring potatoes, mixing well. Add shoestring potatoes right before serving.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Add enough water to make 4 gallons. Just before serving add 2 liter lemon lime soda.

title: grandma betsy's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter;
add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add
to creamed mixture.
Chill thoroughly (3 to 4 hours).
Roll out on well-floured surface to 1/4 to 1/8 inch thickness.	Cut
in
desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: deer recipe
directions: Mix all soups together and combine with 6 cans of water.
Cook on top of stove for 30 minutes.
Add deer meat and cook in a 270° oven for 12 to 15 hours.
Remove from oven and place on stove without lid at low temperature to cook gravy to desired thickness.

title: baked tomato au gratin
directions: In large
greased pie plate or 13 x 9-inch pan, arrange the zucchini
slices.
Top
with
the onions and bread crumbs. Sprinkle garlic
over top. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lay Swiss cheese
slices
over	all
and sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over
all.
Put
tomato slices on top and put remaining 1/4 cup of Parmesan over tomatoes.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter in medium saucepan.
Pour this mixture on top of Rice Chex.
Put mixture in paper sack or grocery bag.
Pour confectioners sugar into bag and shake, shake, shake!

title: coconut-bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 24 muffin pan cups (2 1/2 to 3-inch) or line muffin pan with paper baking cups. Set aside.

title: valentine punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Serves about 20 people.

title: aunt nora's best pralines
directions: Use a large pan and mix first 4 ingredients.
Put candy thermometer in place.
Cook over high heat 5 minutes or to 210°, stirring frequently and scraping bottom.
Add butter and 2 1/3 cup of pecan halves.
Cook, stirring continuously, and scraping bottom and sides of pan, until a little mixture dropped in cold water forms a very soft ball (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat. Stand by while mixture cools slightly; just a couple of minutes. Then, beat with spoon until thickened and creamy.
Immediately drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Dot each piece with a perfect pecan half.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Heat chocolate and half and half in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Pour into fondue pot or chafing dish to keep warm.
Dip fruit or other dippers into chocolate mixture with fondue forks or wooden skewers.

title: barbecue hamburgers and baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Cook on the grill or broiler until done to your rareness.
Add a slice of low-fat cheese until melted.
Serve hamburger roll (preferred potato roll) ketchup, mustard, pickles, tomatoes.
Warm up beans.
Put on plate.
Enjoy.

title: hershey's kisses cookies
directions: Blend together shortening, sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, egg, milk and vanilla until creamy.
Add flour, soda and salt, mixing by hand.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes; remove from oven and place one Hershey's Kiss in the middle of each cookie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, margarine, flour, flavoring and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except Kisses. Mix on low speed until dough forms. Shape into small balls. Roll into sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from oven and top with "Kiss" immediately. Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.
Keep dough in refrigerator in order to roll into balls easily.

title: sunday pork chops
directions: Mix together rice, soup and milk and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Lay the pork chops on top of rice mixture and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tahatian salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and from 1 can of mandarin oranges; add to pudding mix.
Add drained fruit, sliced bananas and marshmallows.
Sprinkle with coconut and chill.

title: non-alcoholic strawberry daiquiri
directions: Combine mixer, strawberries, juices and sugar in a large container and stir to blend.
Pour half of the mix into blender. Add 1/2 c. of ice.
Blend until frothy.
Repeat with remaining mix and ice.

title: candice's cream cheese danish
directions: Roll out (without dividing) one package of rolls into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolk, vanilla and 1 cup sugar. Spread over rolls.
Cover cream cheese mixture with second package of rolls.
Roll out as you did with first layer.
Beat egg white lightly and spread over top of rolls.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar (can use 1/4 cup sugar).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maid of honor potato casserole
directions: Boil cubed potatoes (with skins on) until tender. Cook and drain sausage until it looks like hamburger. Combine butter, grated cheese, cream cheese, pepper, onions, green onions, Parmesan cheese, milk, sausage, salt, pepper and cooked potatoes in large bowl or pan. Place in large casserole dish or baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Top with remaining cheese and cook for another 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: dream dessert
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press down with a fork or use hands.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Brown hamburger in oil.
Add onion, garlic, tomato paste (diluted with water), salt, pepper and bay leaves; simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli and onion in margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients with broccoli and onion.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla together. Roll into balls and refrigerate until firm. Melt chocolate in double boiler and dip balls in chocolate with a toothpick. Put on wax paper until cool.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix ingredients. Shape into 4 loaves and dust in flour.
Place into baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350° or until brown. Remove from oven and make gravy.

title: party chicken wings
directions: Line a baking pan with aluminum foil.
Spray with a no-stick spray.
Lay in chicken wings.
Mix coating ingredients and drizzle over wings.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour, then turn wings over and bake for 1/2 hour to 40 minutes.

title: party fruit salad
directions: Whip cream into soft peaks.
Add sugar and almond extract; beat until stiff.
Fold in yogurt.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve on a tray with fruit.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Then add vinegar, vanilla and melted oleo.
Last, add coconut and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Touch top of pie with finger to see if it is firm.
Good hot or cold.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water or juice.
Add sherbet and get cold.
Then whip or fold in whipped cream.
Put in mold and refrigerate.
The more whipped cream used, the better.
You can also substitute apricot jello and frozen strawberries, using vanilla ice cream and whipped cream.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer bouillon cubes in water.
Add other ingredients except cheese.
Cook about 35 minutes until vegetables are soft.
Then add American Cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: taco noodle bake
directions: Brown meat.
Add seasoning and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix together cooked noodles, drained cottage cheese, onions and green pepper.
Spray oblong baking dish.
Put in noodle mixture.
Top with meat sauce.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes covered.
Remove cover and add grated cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: chili verde
directions: Dice the onions the size to suit your eyes.
Dice carrot, peppers and celery; cook this mixture in oil with 1 to 1/4 ratio of oil to olive oil (1/4 the amount of olive oil versus vegetable oil).
Cook until there is no crunch to the onions.
Insert the mushrooms; cook for another 3 1/2 minutes.
Mix the mushroom soup with equal amount of water; puree it in the mixer.
Pour the jalapeno sauce and soup into the mixture; heat it up, stove-wise. Dice up the pork; cook until it is browned all the way through. Salt and pepper lightly to taste.
Make sure the meat is thoroughly cooked.
Mix the onion mixture in with the meat; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: steak bake
directions: Place potatoes in baking bag. Place meat on top of potatoes. Sprinkle soup mix over all. Seal bag and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: fondant(centers for candy to be dipped)
directions: Centers for candy to be dipped in coatings.
Flavor fondant with any flavor (mint, pecan, maple, coconut, cherry, peanut butter, etc.).
Shape into small balls, refrigerate for a while then dip in melted coating.
Let drain and cool.

title: quick marinated vegetables
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
Mix all vegetables.
Pour salad dressing, 1 cup at a time, until all vegetables are covered.
Refrigerate in an airtight container for 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: lo-cal cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well with a spoon. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake about 50 to 60 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean at 325°.
Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: ripe tomato catsup
directions: Cut up vegetables and drain.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook and seal.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Shape into balls; brown in margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients; place meatballs in sauce.
Simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: service dog recipe
directions: Receive 8-week old puppy.
Take to warm, loving foster care home to raise, teach and love.

title: ma's cherry pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Spread evenly in greased shallow pan. Arrange cherries on top.
Bring sauce to boil and pour over cherries.
Bake at once for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with whipped cream or sour cream.

title: mint drops
directions: Boil sugar and water until it threads.
Pour onto stiffly beaten egg whites and beat with cream of tartar until stiff enough to drop from a spoon.
Add mint.
Use 2 teaspoons together and drop onto buttered marble slab or dish.

title: duxbury pie
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in mincemeat.
Cool.
Put in pie shell.
Cover with lattice work or strips.
Bake at 400° until juices bubble, about 35 to 45 minutes.
Delicious at Thanksgiving or Christmas.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Mix everything in a big pot and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. This fills you up and not out.
Serves 8.
Has 35 calories, 0 fat, food exchanges equals 1/2 vegetable.

title: big boy pie
directions: Brown meat; add onions, ketchup and salt; set aside.
Stir milk into Bisquick and mix until well blended.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead 6 times.
Roll in 9-inch pie plate. Fill with meat mixture.
Cover with tomatoes and top with cheese.
Bake at 375°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peppermint patties
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and extract until smooth. Gradually add confectioners sugar, beating well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on waxed paper-lined baking sheets. Flatten into patties. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or until chilled.

title: baked vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients in a flat baking dish (non-aluminum). Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and add water. Sprinkle dry onion soup over mixture.
Season chicken to taste. Place skin side up on rice mixture.
Slightly dilute mushroom and chicken soups with milk.
Spread on top of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: microwave chicken and rice
directions: Put rice, mushroom soup, milk and mushroom mixture into 8 x 10-inch pan.
Season chicken breasts and lay on top.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Bake in microwave on Full power for 28 minutes, turning halfway through.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add lemon juice.
Stir in condensed milk thoroughly.
Pour into cooled pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Salt lightly and brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Put meat in cake pan or baking dish.
Mix soup with 1/3 can of water and spread on meat.
Cover with cheese slices. Top with Tater Tots. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add green chillies and tomatoes.
Simmer until heated.
Add cheese and salt.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Pour into chafing dish to keep hot. Serve with nacho chips.

title: open-faced cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cream together until smooth the cream cheese, mayonnaise and grated onion.
Cut bread with biscuit cutter or use square rye bread.
Spread mixture on bread.
Peel and slice cucumbers.
Place slices on top and serve as soon as possible.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In electric skillet, brown meat; drain.
Pour 1/3 cup water, both cans of tomatoes, pepper, onion and shredded cabbage.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: You will need a 1-gallon size electric ice cream freezer.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Pare and slice potatoes. Peel and slice onions.
In greased Pyrex bowl, layer potatoes, onions and ham.
Sprinkle with flour. Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Add milk to within 1-inch of top of bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: vegetable chicken loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: cherry-pineapple crisp
directions: Line baking dish (9 x 12-inch) with cherry pie filling.
Cover with drained, crushed pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over pineapple.
Melt margarine and drizzle over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be served warm.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cinnamon together.
Slice apples and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with them (save some apples to put between biscuits).
Roll biscuits in sugar mixture and lay on top of apples.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: angel bars
directions: Combine pie filling and dry cake mix.
Pour into 10 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: coleslaw with pineapple
directions: Shred cabbage.
Pare and shred carrots.
Mix drained pineapple and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Combine cabbage, carrots, mayonnaise, garlic salt and pepper.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: individual pecan pies
directions: Mix brown sugar and syrup well.
Add melted margarine, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Fill pie shells with syrup mixture to 2/3 full.
Put 1 tablespoon chopped pecans on top of each pie.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown and set in middle.
Yields 12 to 14 pies or 1 regular size pie.

title: chicken for a crowd
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute chicken, celery and onion with a small amount of butter until celery and onion are soft.
Mix soup and mayo.
Spread soup and mayo combination onto chicken, celery and onion in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt down rest of butter.
Let cool.
Put 3 eggs in butter and whip.
Mix with stuffing.
Spread over chicken.
Seal in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cut beets in slices or cubes.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water; boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets to hot sauce and let stand at least 30 minutes.
Just before serving, bring to a boil and add butter.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Drain all juice into blender.
Add all ingredients except the pineapple to the blender.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Put pineapple into 9-inch pie plate or baking dish to form crust. Pour blended mixture over pineapple and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and bananas.
Add butter, eggs, soda, salt, flour and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan, 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: italian casserole(serves 8 to 12)
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to package directions.
Brown ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, garlic salt, parsley flakes and salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°. Shape dough into balls and dip top into granulated sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients
except candies in large saucepan. Heat until serving
temperature,
add
candies
and dissolve. Makes 16 one-cup servings.

title: kay's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion, pepper
and
mushrooms after frying bacon. Brown meat in butter.
Add
chili sauce,	catsup and tomatoes. Heat well and then
add
tablespoon
sugar and 1 tablespoon flour. Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green chili stew
directions: Put 1/4 cup oil in skillet; brown meat.
Add flour and transfer into large pot.
Add green chilies, stewed tomatoes (jalapenos or Ro-Tel if you want it hot) and salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Cook over low heat until done.
Serve over rice or whatever or nothing at all.

title: reed and maddie's chocolate pretzels
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in a double boiler.
Careful!
Chocolate burns easily.
Stir constantly.
When melted, remove from heat. Dip rods almost halfway in chocolate.
Roll in bowls of whichever topping is desired.

title: onion pie
directions: Gently saute the onions in the butter until they are limp. Line the bottom of the pie shell with the cooked onions.
Whip together the eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over the onions. Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: sopa de ajo blanco
directions: Crush garlic.
Be sure all bits of skin have been removed. Crush the almonds in a blender or with a mortar and pestle. (Calorie and cholesterol conscious may use 1 heaping tablespoonful crushed Grape-Nuts.)

title: salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon and combine other ingredients.
Blend well. Chill 1 hour.
Shape into patties and dip into extra stuffing mix. Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Drop in a plastic bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Shake until biscuits are well coated and take up all sugar.
Drop into Bundt pan.
If using nuts, layer them and the biscuits.
Boil margarine, sugar and cinnamon for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over biscuits and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes and turn onto plate.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Rack beef to edge of skillet and put onion and green pepper in middle of skillet. Cook for 3 or 4 minutes. Stir meat, onion and pepper together.
Add salt and pepper; stir in macaroni.
Add tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce; stir.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is cooked to suit your taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: madelyne's mini cheesecakes
directions: You will need candy liners (miniature cupcake liners). Purchase at some supermarkets or gourmet or party stores.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Pour in peaches and juice.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour around over peaches. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together well.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Now add flour alternately with buttermilk and vanilla in which soda has been dissolved.
Fold in beaten egg whites and add coconut and pecans.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layers in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and honey, then beat in the egg, vanilla and pumpkin.
Stir together the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with salt until tender; debone and chop.
Add chopped onion and cubed Velveeta cheese.
Mix the cream soups with 2 cups broth and chopped pepper.
Crush Doritos and add all but enough to sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 300° until thickened.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix and press evenly into 9-inch pie dish. Bake at 375° until light brown. Makes 1 crust.

title: baked chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients and 1 cup cheese in a large bowl until well blended. Wrap tortillas in plastic wrap. Heat in microwave according to package directions. Spoon chicken mixture down center of each warm tortilla; roll up. Place in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook diced tomatoes, tomato sauce and cream in a saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring often, 10 minutes. Pour tomato mixture over tortillas, spreading evenly to all ends. Sprinkle with remaining 2 cups cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and tomato mixture is bubbly. Serve with desired toppings.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Cut the steaks into small cubes.
Sear and brown in bacon drippings.
Add pepper, tomatoes, onions and potatoes, all cut into wedges.
Pour the beef gravy or stock made from bouillon cubes over steak.
Cover skillet and steam at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger and orange peel.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Separately combine undrained pineapple, eggs, butter or margarine and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Turn out on rack to cool.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a heavy skillet, caramelize one of the cups of sugar over a very low heat.
Slowly bring to a boil the other 2 cups of sugar, salt, corn syrup and milk; boil 3 minutes.
Slowly add the caramelized sugar to the boiling mixture.
Cook until it forms a soft ball when tested in cool water or cook to 236°.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Allow to cool to lukewarm, without stirring. Add vanilla; beat candy until it begins to thicken.
Add pecans and coconut and continue to beat until candy holds its shape when dropped on waxed paper.

title: "witch's brew"
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl for 2 minutes.
Bring apple juice to boil; add cinnamon sticks.
Add the dissolved gelatin to apple juice and serve while hot.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Crumble sausage and mix with cheese.
Add biscuit mix, one cup at a time.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
(May be frozen at this stage.)
Bake in preheated oven about 13 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
If frozen, cooking may take a few extra minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: betty's christmas salad
directions: Warm to room temperature and beat the cream cheese.
Drain pineapple, but save juice.
Use 1 cup of boiling water and 1 cup pineapple juice (water added to make 1 cup) to make jello.
Add warm cheese and beat it on medium speed on mixer in small deep bowl into the jello until smooth.
Fold in pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Turn into 6-cup jello mold which has been sprayed with Pam.
Chill overnight.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix with chopped or shredded cabbage and carrots to taste.

title: pickled squash
directions: Bring to a boil.
Drain ice water off of vegetables.
Add to syrup mixture and boil 3 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill and combine apple juice, pineapple juice, Seven-Up and cranberry juice.
Add ice ring made of cranberry juice and fruit cocktail to keep cold while serving.

title: chicken-in-a-garden
directions: Mix ingredients using 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add onion rings to top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: elna's chicken
directions: Put chicken in one layer in a baking dish.
Mix sauce ingredients in a bowl and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover loosely with foil if chicken begins to brown.
Goes well with rice and steamed broccoli.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix and bring to a boil the first five ingredients.
Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 3/4 cup peanut butter.
Stir in 3 cups rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool and serve.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: speedy chicken stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except bagel chips in Dutch oven.
Heat to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chicken is no longer pink in the center and vegetables are tender.
Top with bagel chips.
Yields 4.

title: pear relish
directions: Cut pears small. Grind onions and peppers then combine all ingredients. Bring to boiling point and cook 30 minutes or until mixture is thick as desired. Seal in clean jars while hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until smooth.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour and beat until flour is used up.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Notice this does not use milk or flavoring.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread as directed.
Crumble in large bowl.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Chill.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and put into a casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: baked fish with tomato sauce
directions: Combine onion, celery and parsley.
Put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay fish on top of vegetables.
Sprinkle fish with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Brush fish with oil or butter.
Pour tomato sauce on top and bake 30 minutes more.

title: lacy no-fry latkes
directions: Place oven racks on the lowest and middle positions in oven. Preheat oven to 450°.
Line two baking sheets with aluminum foil. Spray each baking sheet lightly with nonstick vegetable spray. Brush each baking sheet with one teaspoon of the oil.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Combine cheese, beaten eggs, jalapenos and onion in bowl; mix well.
Spread in ungreased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares. Yield:
36 servings.

title: oatmeal balls
directions: Cut together with a fork until well mixed.
Roll into balls and roll in confectioners sugar and ground nuts.
Refrigerate. Makes 24 balls.

title: dottie's salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O together.
Pour in mold or casserole dish.
Mix
pineapple,
Cool Whip and fruit cocktail. Put onto cottage
cheese
mixture and put into refrigerator and chill for about 5 to 6 hours or more.

title: laura's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together; add to banana mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter in prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bread tests done. Bread stays moist because of buttermilk.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and cool (do not overcook). Mix everything together, pouring dressing over all. Better if it sits an hour or so. Stirring once in a while.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, celery soup and sour cream together. Prepare stuffing as package directs.
Spread stuffing on bottom of greased casserole.
Add squash mixture on top of stuffing and top with grated cheese.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, cornstarch, sugar and salt; make a well in the middle of dry ingredients.
Slowly blend in the buttermilk with a wooden spoon.
Knead and shape on floured board into 2 or 3 loaves.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Cut cross in top of bread before baking in a preheated 375° oven.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: lima grande casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Place a layer of large lima beans in bottom of dish; dot with prepared mustard and catsup and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer beans with bacon bits.
Continue with two more layers as before.
Cover all with Log Cabin (or other) maple syrup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion and garlic.
Cook spinach and drain, reserving liquid, and add water to make 1 cup.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add to meat mixture.
Combine spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and pepper and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine cooked spinach with cooked macaroni and add to tomato sauce mixture along with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs, eggs and oil and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oleta houston's dill pickles
directions: Bring the water, vinegar and salt to a boil. Wash and dry cucumbers and pack in clean jars. Drop alum into each jar along with garlic, dill and hot peppers, if desired.
Pour hot mixture over cucumbers and seal.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: special cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Oil baking dish.
Bake 375 for 45 minutes.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat chicken broth, salt and white pepper to boiling.
Stir green onion into eggs.
Pour egg mixture slowly into broth, stirring constantly, with fork until eggs form shreds.

title: hot chicken salad #2
directions: Mix all ingredients except for potato chips.
Pour into shallow baking dish and spread crushed potato chips over top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve very hot with cranberry sauce and rolls.

title: quick muffins
directions: Stir all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cook eggplant until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix in order given.
Pour into baking dish and top with toasted bread crumbs mixed with 1/4 stick oleo.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: german chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up chicken into pieces (salt).
Put in a large pot and cover with water.
(If you want a clear broth, just add three or four chicken breasts.)
Add onion.
Cook, covered, until tender. Remove the chicken from the pot and remove any bones.
Cut up chicken in pieces or add the chicken just the way it is back to the pot.
While the chicken has been cooking, make the dumplings, as follows:

title: "guilt-free" sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until combined.

Gradually add egg substitute, beating well. Combine sour cream and baking soda; stir well, and set aside. Combine flour and salt; with mixer running at low speed, add to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into a 10-inch tube pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: spinach pom poms
directions: Squeeze spinach in hands until dry.
Place all ingredients in a medium bowl and blend together.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Refrigerate or freeze (if not, use right away).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until hot.
Drain on paper towels.

title: hamburger-noodle bake
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain off fat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
As this cooks, mix together green onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
In oven dish, alternate layer of meat mixture, noodles and cream cheese.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: chicken wonder
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add flour and milk; mix together. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and mushrooms.
Mix together cooked rice and more mushrooms (if you would like).
Layer rice and chicken; cook in small casserole dish. Top with sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Boil milk and flour until thick, then cool.
Beat in butter, Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Beat all ingredients until fluffy.

title: chicken breasts autumn
directions: In a large skillet, saute apples in 1 tablespoon margarine. Add brown sugar; cook about 3 minutes.
Remove apples; set aside. Add onion; saute until opaque.
Remove onion.
Add remaining margarine to pan; brown chicken breasts.
Remove and place in baking dish.
To the pan drippings, add chicken broth, wine and yogurt.
After whisking them together, simmer for 2 to 3 minutes. Add apples and onion.
Pour mixture over chicken; bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil milk, butter and sugar for 9 minutes.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallow and nuts.
Pour in a big pan.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, brown sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soap balls
directions: Mix together; roll into balls.
Great for kids in summer to wash with fun.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in halves, lengthwise, and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks with mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients, except paprika, stirring well.
Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture. Garnish eggs with paprika.

title: cider sherbet refresher
directions: Pour the chilled cider over the sherbet which has been spooned into a punch bowl.
Just before serving pour the carbonated beverage in gently.
Garnish with sprigs of mint.
Makes 12 servings.

title: quick corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pimiento, in pan and mix well. Heat thoroughly.
Add pimiento.
Cool and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Remove skin from chicken pieces.
Brown in olive oil.
Add garlic, minced. When chicken is browned, add the following: onions, garlic, both peppers, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Simmer until all are soft.
Add red wine.
Add oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer until consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Add more wine if too thick.
Add either black olives or green (pitted).
Before serving, add 1/2 cup grated Locatelli cheese.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Boil carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Mix and bring to a boil the sugar, oil, vinegar, dry mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Add soup and blend until smooth.
Add green
pepper and onion to carrots.
Pour sauce over and marinate 24 hours.

title: caramel apple delight(used for dipping apples)
directions: Blend using a mixer. Serve with fresh sliced apples.

title: lemony light cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine juice, sugar and ReaLemon juice; stir until dissolves.
Just before serving, add club soda and fruit; serve over ice in a pretty glass.
Makes about 7 cups.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: zucchini cheese puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place zucchini in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with flour and 1 cup of the Swiss cheese.
In large bowl, combine sour cream and egg yolks.
Add 1/4 cup bread crumbs, chives, salt and pepper; blend well.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry.
Fold into sour cream mixture.
Spoon over zucchini.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Swiss cheese, 1 tablespoon bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until puffed, set and golden brown.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Line Twinkies in a cake pan 9 x 12-inch.
Next, put pineapple over Twinkies, then pudding next, bananas on top of pudding and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: cheese log
directions: Grate Longhorn cheese and set until soft.
Mix with cream cheese and rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Form into rolls and roll onto nuts. Wrap into wax paper and chill.
Cut into thin slices and serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Mix fruit cocktail and egg together and add to mixture.
Place in greased square 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: hidden valley ranch crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Mix well. Place crackers in large bowl and pour mixture over, coating well. Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 15 minutes, stirring once.
Let cool.
A great snack.

title: taco in a bowl
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add next 5 ingredients and 1/4 cup green pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer corn chips, ground beef mixture, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onion and green pepper in individual serving bowls.
Top with taco sauce and sour cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup of milk, the meat and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix Bisquick and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in pan.
Mix all other ingredients in mixing bowl and pour into pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until brown.

title: flamingo cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in half, then cut each half in fourths.
Steam cabbage in small amount of water.
Add cranberries in spoonfuls and mix lightly.
Add 2 tablespoons vinegar and stir.
Cook until soft (about 10 minutes), stirring twice.
Recipe may be halved easily.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, egg, soup mix, salt and pepper.
Make meatballs a little smaller than a golf ball.
Brown slightly in pan; remove and drain.
Mix chili sauce and grape jelly together. Add meatballs to mixture and heat slowly for about an hour (crock-pot works best).
Check meatballs for completely done throughout.
Serve hot.

title: different pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar and baking powder. Stir in crumbs and pecans.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream when served.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage until crumbly; drain.
Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Mix with sausage; add chicken noodle soup.
Add water, rice and water chestnuts.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pan with cupcake liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill liners 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Top with teaspoonful of filling.

title: tropical baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and place bacon on top.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Put milk, liquid, mayonnaise, egg and bread in a bowl and beat with egg beater until blended well.
Add all the other ingredients but don't break up the seafood too much.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Chop onion and pepper.
Mix beef, onion, pepper, tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes and add cream of mushroom soup.
Put cheese and Doritos in layers.
Add other mixed ingredients and layer again with cheese and Doritos.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar and rest of ingredients and pour over vegetables. Toss and refrigerate.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: *Sour cream may be substituted.

title: bean vegetable salad
directions: Mix all of vegetables together.*
Heat sugar and vinegar together to boiling, then cool 5 minutes.
Pour vinegar solution over vegetables.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: flower pot cake
directions: Put cookies in Ziploc bag and crush until mixture looks like dirt.
Set aside.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk according to package directions.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies and cream mixture in a deep flower pot lined with aluminum foil or you may use a plastic sand bucket.
Top layer should be cookie (dirt) layer.
Decorate flower pot with an artificial flower and decorate plastic sand bucket with plastic sand shovel.

title: oven baked herb chicken
directions: Combine onion salad dressing mix, butter and paprika with a spatula.
Spread mixture over chicken pieces.
Roll in dry bread crumbs to coat.
Bake in greased pan at 375° about 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter	8
slices
of bread and cut into 1/2-inch cubes and reserve.
Cut
another 8 slices into 1-inch cubes.	Place half of unbuttered cubes (4 slices) in a 16 x 16 x 4-inch pan or
divide into
(8-inch)
square
pans.
Combine chicken, vegetables, mayonnaise	and
seasonings;
spoon
over
bread. Sprinkle remaining
unbuttered
cubes
over	chicken mixture. Combine eggs and milk and pour over all.
Chill for 1 hour or overnight.
Spoon soup
over
top
during last few minutes of baking.
Serves
12. Bake
at
325° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top during last few minutes of baking.

title: salt-flour clay
directions: Combine salt and flour with your hands.
Mix and knead in enough water to make a stiff dough.
Tint with food coloring or tempera paint.
Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.

title: hearty duck and bean casserole(from ducks unlimited)
directions: Soak beans in water and cover overnight.
Drain.
Combine with 2 quarts water in saucepan.
Rinse duck breast.
Add duck, cloves and bay leaves to beans.
Bring to a boil; skim off foam.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cook beans for 15 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaves. Drain liquid and reserve for later use.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Chop onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Add tomato sauce, Velveeta and mushrooms.
Turn on low heat and stir occasionally until cheese is melted and all ingredients are heated.
Slice French bread into thin slices (1/2-inch) and spoon mixture on top.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
After frozen, put in bags for later use.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and salt.
Let cook until tender; drain well and mash.
When mashed, add next 4 ingredients, then melt oleo and stir in crumbs until coated well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with 3/4 of the crumbs.
Pour squash mixture over these, then add the remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creole hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Then add the onion and green pepper and cook for a few minutes longer.
Add all the remaining ingredients to the hamburger, onion and pepper.
Put in covered casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lois drum's toll house cookies
directions: Cream shortening until smooth.
Add sugars and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mix after each one.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and oats.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: nuclear chili
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Brown the hot sausage and drain. Add to meat, tomato paste, water, onion and all peppers.
Drain and rinse kidney beans; add to mixture.
Add all other ingredients.
Leave in crock-pot on low 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with plenty of cold water.

title: fisherman's wharf swordfish
directions: Cut the fish into 4 serving pieces, each about 6 ounces.
In a heavy large skillet saute the onion and garlic in the oil until softened but not browned.
Stir in the tomatoes, green peppers, salt, pepper and water, broth or wine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for about 10 minutes.
Add the swordfish. Cover.
Cook over simmering heat for 8 to 10 minutes until cooked. Serve fish, spooned with vegetables and juice.

title: cheese spread
directions: Microwave on High, oleo, flour, milk, egg, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Stir every 2 minutes until thick.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Microwave for a few seconds, if needed to melt cheese. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: artichoke soup
directions: Saute shallots and onion in butter and olive oil.
Add mushroom soup, cream and water.
Break artichoke hearts.
Add juice.
Chop oysters.
Add juice, Italian cheese, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 30 minutes and let stand another 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: heath bar chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on box.
Let cake completely cool at least 3 hours.
Poke holes all over the cake (all the way through).
I used the handle of wooden spoon.
Next, pour first the Eagle Brand milk and then the topping over the cake so that they both go into the holes.
Spread Cool Whip over the entire cake.
Sprinkle Heath bars (crushed) over the Cool Whip. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Crush candy by putting in plastic bag and beating with rolling pin (or hammer).

title: quick little pizzas
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon soup on each muffin half.
Sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Place 4 muffin halves in paper towel-lined oblong glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through, turning dish once.
Repeat with remaining muffin halves.

title: hummus
directions: Use 1/2 cup of water; add sesame seed and blend well in blender.
Add garbanzos, olive oil and garlic powder.
Salt to taste.
If the mixture is too thick, you can add the amount of water necessary to get the consistency you like.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pumpkin, and fry until tender. Cut top off pumpkin and clean out. Add the cooked ingredients to pumpkin and bake at 350° for 1 hour with lid on pumpkin. You may eat the pumpkin meat. It is similar to squash and children love scooping dinner from a pumpkin. This could be a tradition for Halloween night.

title: polish cabbage rolls
directions: Saut hamburger, pork and onion.
Season with salt and pepper and drain.
In large kettle, boil cabbage (without the core) for 3-4 minutes.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Rinse with cold water and remove leaves.
Roll meat mixture in cabbage leaves.
Remove first 4 leaves and place 2 on the bottom of the large kettle.
Layer 3/4 c. sauerkraut, then cabbage rolls and either tomato sauce or tomatoes over the top.
Add 1 c. water.
Put other 2 large leaves on top.
Cover with plate and put small jar on top to hold plate down.
Bring to boil and then turn heat to low.
Cook 1-1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and pull apart the broccoli.
Fry and crumble the bacon. Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add salt.
Mix dressing and pour over all salad ingredients.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine
flour,
sugar and cocoa.
Melt butter and pour in flour mixture.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 370° for 30 minutes.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Process mustard, mustard seed, honey, vinegar and salt.
Cover and let stand overnight for the flavor to develop.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook margarine, sugar, egg, dates and salt together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Stir well and shape in small balls.
Roll in flaked coconut.

title: dijon-glazed chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Coat grill rack with vegetable cooking spray; place on grill over medium hot coals.
Place chicken on rack, brushing half of glaze mixture over chicken.
Cook 5 minutes; turn chicken and brush with remaining glaze.
Cook an additional 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Transfer chicken to a serving platter.
Garnish with fresh parsley sprigs, if desired.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Soften margarine; add the rest of ingredients.
Spread mixture on both sides of rolls.
Put ham and cheese on rolls.
Warm at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole with cooking spray.
Mix eggs and sugar in casserole.
Add pineapple and mix.
Cover top with crushed Ritz crackers; dot with butter.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1/2 hour.
Good with ham.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: linguine florentine
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly.
Cook spinach covered in large Dutch oven over medium heat 4 minutes or until tender (do not add water).
Drain well; finely chop leaves and set aside.
Cook linguine; drain.
Combine linguine and olive oil in large bowl; toss gently.
Add spinach, cheese and pepper; toss gently.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Yields 9 servings.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender; drain.
Add carrots.
Mash on low speed with electric mixer; slowly beat in enough milk to make light.
Stir in margarine and a little salt and pepper.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with additional margarine, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit, assorted cheeses or cookies as dippers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk together and add to the cream cheese mixture. Gradually blend in Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.
Spread 1/3 of cookies on bottom of serving container.
Spoon cream mixture over crushed cookies.
Continue to layer until cookies and mixture are gone.
Save enough crushed cookies to make the top look like "dirt."

title: miniature cheesecakes(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin tins with paper baking cups.
Place vanilla wafer in each cup.
Beat remaining ingredients together until light and fluffy.
Fill cups 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with sour or whipped cream, nuts, fruit or shaved chocolate.

title: slick dumplings
directions: Beat ingredients well.
Blend in 1 cup (more or less) of flour with a fork.
Shape into round balls and roll out until dough is about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in squares and put into boiling broth.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut sugar cookies in 1-inch slices and place in a pizza pan. Use any remaining dough to fill in spaces between cookies.
Bake according to instructions.
While cookies are baking, mix cream cheese with a little sugar and vanilla until thinned.
Spread over cooled cookies.
Layer pineapple tidbits, oranges and bananas. Mix strawberries with the glaze and spread on top of layered fruit.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until foamy.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients and add to the liquid, beating well.
Add nuts and seeds.
Divide batter into two greased and floured loaf pans (1 pound size).
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 325° oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.
This bread will freeze well.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot water; set aside to cool. Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well. Add 3 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir melted chocolate into butter mixture. Add flour, salt, nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla, stirring well. Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half.
Clean.
Boil until tender (4 to 5 minutes).
Brown beef.
Add seasoning.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, onion and corn.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat 9 x 13-inch pan and oven to 350°.

title: chow mein noodle-tuna hot dish
directions: Mix tuna, mushroom soup and peas together and heat thoroughly. Spread chow mein noodles.

title: sauce for pork chops
directions: Mix ingredients. Add meat. Let meat (pork chops, chicken, rabbit or moose ribs) cook until tender.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Steam broccoli.
Boil rice in water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients with Cheez Whiz and soup.
Bake in greased casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: city chicken
directions: Alternate veal and pork cubes on 6 wooden skewers.
Dip in crumbs, then in eggs and again in crumbs.
Brown on all sides in hot fat in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from skillet and place in pan or baking dish.
Add a little water and bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Can be eaten cold.
Excellent for a picnic.

title: good easy dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O until dissolved.
Drain berries.
Puree berries in blender.
Stir into gelatin along with lemon juice.
Chill until thick as unbeaten egg white.
While mixture chills, cut jelly rolls into 1/4-inch slices.
Line a 2-quart mixing bowl with plastic wrap.
Arrange jelly roll slices close together to line bowl.
Fold whipped cream into thickened strawberry mixture until no streaks of white remain.
Spoon mixture into jelly roll-lined bowl.
Chill until firm, about 3 to 4 hours.
Unmold dessert on serving plate.
Remove plastic wrap. You can substitute an 8 ounce carton of Cool Whip for the whipping cream.

title: aunt vivian's soup
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Bring ground chuck, onion, succotash, cabbage and tomatoes to a boil; simmer 15 minutes.
Add macaroni and 1/2 to 1 quart of water.
Simmer until vegetables are tender. Season to taste.

title: classic pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled margarine and anise seed.
Sift flour and baking powder. Blend into egg mixture with wooden spoon until smooth.
Dough will be sticky.
Bake in pizzelle baker about 1 minute (1 teaspoon batter per side).
Makes approximately 60 pizzelles.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into marble-sized balls.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Drain grease and cook until brown in oven.

title: baked greek freighter meat pie
directions: Brown beef in oil and butter over medium heat; add onion, potatoes and garlic.
Add salt at beginning and rest of spices at end.
Let cool and drain off oil and toss in Feta cheese.
Lay 1/4 package phyllo in 8-inch square (or I use an 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish) oiling between layers.
Place meat mixture on top of phyllo, then spread spinach on top.
Then follow with Egg Custard.
Fold overlapping phyllo over top and dust with cinnamon and drizzle on butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Let sit for a time before cutting.
(Watch, as it might seep over in oven.)

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Pour
into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (325°glass). Check, bakes faster sometimes.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add a little juice from cherries to make a paste.
Add remaining cherry juice and pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat until thickened. Add Jell-O, bananas, pecans and coloring.
Pour in graham cracker crusts and let congeal.
Top with Cool Whip.
May be frozen for later use.

title: tropical fruit drink
directions: Put first 7 ingredients into blender; finish filling blender to top with ice.
Blend until smooth.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oats, flour and brown sugar. Cut in butter until crumbly. Place half this mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with cranberry mixture (grated cranberries, orange and sugar). Top with balance of crumb mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef pie
directions: Brown and drain beef. Stir in remaining ingredients except egg and cheese.

title: fire house beans
directions: Cook onions in one half cup of water until tender.
Then add bacon and brown sugar; fry for 15 minutes.
Mix with all of the beans.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: joan's four star chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in baking pan in one layer.
Sprinkle generously with fresh ginger and garlic.
Cover with equal parts of dry sherry and soy sauce.
Cover; marinate in the refrigerator for at least 6 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken wings, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: pineapple shrimp in croustades
directions: Melt butter.
Add shrimp until coated.
Sprinkle with cornstarch, stirring until well blended.
Add seasonings.
Stir in cream slowly.
Heat, stirring until mixture bubbles and thickens. Stir in sour cream slowly.
Add sherry.
Drain pineapple and gently stir into mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve in patty shells.

title: white pizza
directions: Line 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans with crescent rolls.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix in a bowl.
Spread over dough. Bake at 375° for 11 minutes.
Cool and top with chopped broccoli, cauliflower, celery, olives, carrots, onions, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, etc.
Be sure everything is well drained.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: reese cup cookies
directions: Slice cookie dough and cut into quarters.
Place each quarter in mini-muffin tins.
Put peanut butter cup on top.
Bake according to directions on cookie dough packaging (time and temperature).
Peanut butter cookie dough can also be used. Enjoy!

title: vienna-style veal cutlets(wiener schnitzel)
directions: Pound cutlets lightly; trim meat as needed.
Clip or slash edges to prevent curling during cooking.
Sprinkle each cutlet lightly with lemon juice and salt; coat with flour.
In a small shallow bowl, beat together egg and water.
Dip cutlets in egg mixture; coat with breadcrumbs.
Melt butter in a medium skillet. Fry cutlets in butter until golden brown.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: tracy's custard pie
directions: Stir all other ingredients into scalded milk until well dissolved.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: venison burgundy
directions: Sprinkle each steak with 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1/8 teaspoon parsley flakes and rub each with rosemary.
Brown on both sides in butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Add wine and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add more wine, if necessary, during cooking. Remove the meat from the skillet and stir in the can of mushroom soup.
Bring to a boil and pour this over the steaks.

title: 300 waldorf cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs.
Make a paste of the coloring and cocoa and add to sugar mixture.
Add salt, buttermilk, vanilla, vinegar and soda.
Blend in the flour slowly. Bake in 2 (8 x 8-inch) cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend flour, confectioners sugar and butter together.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked rice
directions: Pour 1 c. raw rice in casserole dish.
Season with salt & pepper.
Pour 1 c. tomato juice over rice.
Chop 1/2 c. of onion, peppers, or celery.
Add 1 lb. raw ground beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1 1/2 c. tomato juice and 1/4 c. water over it.

title: spicy apple twists
directions: Cut apples into 8 wedges each.
Sift salt and flour; cut in shortening.
Sprinkle cold water over; mix well.
Form ball; roll out to 16 (1 x 10-inch) strips.
Wrap one strip around each apple wedge.
Arrange in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Pour water around pastries. Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: red velvet cocoa cake
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and food coloring.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to margarine mixture.
Stir soda into vinegar. Fold into batter.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crazy beans
directions: Stir all ingredients in with beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Slowly mix all ingredients together. Serve with veggies or chips.

title: macaroni vegetable salad
directions: Drain kidney beans, place in small bowl, cover with vinegar and let set one hour.
Drain.
Cook rotini according to package directions.
In large bowl, combine beans, rotini, and vegetables. Combine salad dressing, half and half, sugar and mustard; mix well.
Pour over rotini mixture and mix lightly.
Chill before serving.

title: country potato soup
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine potatoes, celery, onion, water, bouillon cubes and salt.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes or until tender (do not overcook).
Add 1 cup of the milk.
Mix sour cream, flour and other cup of milk.
Gradually stir sour cream mixture into soup base.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain; beat eggs. Add milk, salt and mustard to eggs while beating.
Into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: shrimp and tuna mold
directions: Bring soup to a boil.
Add cream cheese and melt.
Remove from fire.
Add gelatine, dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Add mayonnaise, celery and onions.
Cool slightly and add the shrimp or the can of tuna.
Put in mold. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: chunky cheese mexican casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions, drain. Crumble beef into skillet.
Add onion, celery and green pepper. Cook and stir until brown; drain.
Stir in olives, undrained tomatoes, beef bouillon and seasoned salt.
Blend well.
Combine macaroni, meat mixture and cheese chunks.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover; heat in 350° oven until cheese melts, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and jello in hot water; add pineapple juice. Set until begins to thicken.
Mix softened cream cheese and mayonnaise; add pineapple, nuts and pinch of salt.
Whip small can of Pet milk, adding a little lemon juice.
Add food coloring as desired.
Mix with mixture and congeal.

title: pig eaten cake
directions: Mix cake as directed; poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon. Mix pudding and pineapple together; pour over cake.
Add Cool Whip.
When cool, refrigerate.

title: brown rice
directions: Put rice in a 2 qt. dish. Pour soup over rice. Put sliced butter on top and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: In a large deep pan, brown ground chuck; drain.
Add onion and cook until onion is transparent.
Add tomato sauce, Velveeta, garlic powder, Worcestershire
sauce, jalapenos and juice.
Heat through but do not boil.
Serve hot.
Makes 20 servings.
Freezes well.

title: alaskan hot crab dip
directions: Mix together crabmeat, cream cheese, sour cream and horseradish sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and smooth over the bottom of the dish. Sprinkle slivered almonds over the top of the dish and finish with a little paprika.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers.
Triscuits seem to complement the dip the best.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water and pineapple juice.
Add pineapple, banana and strawberries.
Put 1/2 in 9 x 13-inch dish and jell. Spread sour cream over and add rest of jello.

title: kahlua
directions: Make a simple syrup of water and sugar.
Cool after adding the instant coffee to room temperature.
Add vanilla and Everclear. Immediately place in glass container to store.
Makes 2 pints or 3 fifths.

title: white bread
directions: Sift flour into a large bowl.
Melt shortening. To shortening, add sugar, salt and 1 cup water. Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water and add to other liquids.
Pour into "well" formed in flour.
Mix with hands until all flour is absorbed.
Knead on flour covered surface.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and allow to rise until doubled in size.
Shape into loaves. Allow to rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from pans to cooling rack. Brush tops with butter for soft crust.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with crackers.
This makes 2 balls.

title: alternative to peanut butter and jelly
directions: For a creamier, sweeter peanut butter, add some Karo syrup. Mix it together with a spoon.
Great on toast!

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Ready to serve.

title: chicken, artichoke and rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions, omitting butter, and allow to cool.
Drain artichokes, saving juice for dressing.
Cut artichokes in halves or slice and add to rice with remaining ingredients.

title: creamy onion soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, saut onions in butter. Add broth, pepper, thyme, salt and bouillon. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes. Add 1 2/3 cups milk. Stir flour into remaining 1/3 cup milk until smooth; add to soup. Bring to boil; boil and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. YIELD: 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt butter and blend in flour, adding 1/2 teaspoon salt, and dash of pepper.
Add chicken broth then cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in cream and wine.

title: marinated beef rib bones or chicken for barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate at least 4 hours.
Barbecue as usual.

title: apple spoon-up
directions: Spread apples in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Separate crescent rolls.
Put rectangles over apples (rectangles need not completely cover apples).
Combine sour cream and brown sugar.
Spread over rectangles.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until deep golden brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Chill 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Crumble and set aside.
In separate pan, melt butter.
Blend in flour and add milk and cream gradually.
Cook unti thick, stirring frequently.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: red velvet cake frosting
directions: In a pan mix milk and flour until hot, then set aside.
In a bowl mix sugar and Wesson oil until blended, then add coconut and nuts and pour over cake.

title: i hate vegetables brussels sprouts
directions: Clean Brussels sprouts.
Put in saucepan with 1/4 cup of water.
Add mushroom soup to can and stir.
Cook over low to medium heat until tender.
