Be careful not to overcook.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
You may add more water if necessary with water chestnuts.
Slice chestnuts thin, about 1/2 cup and cook with ingredients.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
Use as a side dish.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine in a bowl the margarine, brown sugar and sugar; stir until creamy.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet and allow to melt.
Add drained fruit and bananas and chill.
This serves 12-15 people.

title: strawberry shortcake pie
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a saucepan. Bring mixture to a full boil, stirring constantly. Remove pan from heat. Cool for 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Add pound cake and 1 cup of strawberries.
Turn mixture into pie shell.
Chill until set, at least 2 hours. Arrange remaining berries on top of pie before serving.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Cook 2 minutes on High or until butter melts.
Stir until blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour on buttered platter.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet. When bacon is done, remove from pan. Place cabbage in bacon grease and cook until tender. While cabbage is cooking, cook noodles according to package directions. Drain noodles. Mix noodles with crumbled bacon and cabbage. Add desired amount of parsley flakes.

title: adobe pie*
directions: Blend the wafers, butter, and Amaretto.
Press into a pie pan and make into a crust.
Bake in oven at 350 for 6-9 minutes. After removing from oven, freeze for 15 minutes.

title: rich and easy chicken
directions: Skin and rinse chicken breasts.
Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken breasts and bake for 1 1/2 hours in a preheated 350° oven.
Serve with rice.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Melt butter and add flour and salt; cook until bubbly.
Add cream, milk and chicken broth, stirring until smooth.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Serve over rice.

title: apple or peach strudel
directions: Place apples or peaches in the bottom of a buttered baking dish.
(Use more fruit if needed to make a thick layer on the bottom of the baking dish.)
Mix the sugar and cinnamon (to taste) and sprinkle on the fruit.
Dot with lumps of butter.
Mix the remaining dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add egg and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until crust is brown.
Serve with milk, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Make the butter cake mix as on the box.
After you take the cake out of the oven, take a wooden spoon, punch holes in the hot cake.
Then pour the condensed milk and cream of coconut over the hot cake.
Be sure to mix the milk and cream of coconut together first before pouring over the hot cake.
When the cake is completely cold, cream the Cool Whip over the cake and then sprinkle the coconut over the Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator. Ready to eat.

title: cafe diable from the greenbrier(white sulphur springs, west virginia)
directions: While melting sugar in saucepan, squeeze with spoon the lemon and orange rinds into sugar.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of prepared hot coffee.
Add the brandy and ignite.
Pour remaining coffee into flame.
Add Kirsch and cinnamon stick; bring to boil.
Strain and serve piping hot in demitasse.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer in the raw rice and chicken. Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until rice is done.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13 cake pan or Bundt pan. Mix and sprinkle over cake. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut rolls
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine all dry ingredients (except powdered sugar) and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour onto a greased, floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until cake is springy.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until it won't shake in pan.

title: soup base
directions: Mix the first two ingredients as the base and add any or all of the remaining ingredients.
Put all ingredients in a qt. jar and shake to mix.
To use, add 1/3 cup of the mix to one cup of cold water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook each package of noodles.
Drain.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain; cool and break into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Serves 8 to 10.
Serve with tomato slices.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and Italian dressing.
Sour dough crackers are a perfect compliment.

title: brownie-peanut cookies
directions: Add egg, chopped peanuts and peanut butter to mix.
Blend with hands, adding a few drops of water if necessary.
Press and make into long roll about 2 inches in diameter.
Slice 1/8-inch thick. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: veal and noodles
directions: Cut veal into 1-inch cubes.
Brown in shortening.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika; sprinkle over meat and stir until blended.
Add water, Worcestershire, onions, carrots and celery. Cover.
When steaming, cook for 25 minutes on low heat.
Add sliced peppers and cook 5 to 10 minutes more.
Serve meat over cooked noodles tossed in butter.

title: spicy baked chicken
directions: In small bowl, stir together flour, parsley, salad dressing mix, margarine and paprika. Blend in water. Remove wing tips and skin from chicken pieces. Spread flour mixture over skinned chicken pieces. Place chicken in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake in 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Do not turn.

title: spuds a la elegant
directions: Peel, quarter and cook potatoes in boiling, lightly salted water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender; drain.
Mash potatoes. Add cream cheese, egg, salt and dash of pepper; beat until smooth. Stir in onion and pimento.
If mixture seems dry, stir in 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.
Transfer to buttered, 1-quart, round casserole.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into generous meat balls.
Cover with the following sauce.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Boil rice, soup and water for 7 minutes.
Brown sausage.
Lift out with slotted spoon.
Add sausage to mixture.
Brown in sausage drippings the celery, green pepper and onion.
Add to rice mixture.
Put into casserole and cover with almonds.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Layer croutons, cheese and sausage in a casserole dish.
Blend milk and eggs.
Pour over croutons.
Let sit in refrigerate overnight (at least 8 hours), covered.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Layer in following order into bowl:
dates, raisins, then candied fruit.
Add flavorings to juice and pour over dried fruits. Let set a couple hours or overnight.
Mix together oil, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Add 1/2 cup flour, baking powder, salt and spices. Add fruit/flavoring mixture.
Last fold in 3/4 cup flour and nuts. Bake in slow oven at 275° to 300°; check at 1 1/4 hours.
Might take 2 hours to finish.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Place cooked, cut up chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Prepare 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix; make according to directions, adding 1 egg to make a moist stuffing. Sprinkle mixture over chicken.
Mix together the soup and sour cream; spread this mixture over the stuffing.
Best results when made the day before to let the flavors mix while refrigerated overnight before baking.
Bake in an oven at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and softened butter.
Add egg, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together remaining ingredients and blend into creamed mixture.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
I usually mix it up the day before I roll and cut it out.
Roll out on lightly floured surface, 1/8-inch for thin or 1/4-inch for thick.
I usually make them thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Put on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes for thin or 10 to 12 minutes for thick.
Frost or decorate, if desired.

title: divine chicken dijon
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add chicken breasts and cook until done and lightly browned.
Remove chicken to platter and keep warm.
Stir flour into drippings in the skillet and cook, stirring, about 1 minute.
Add the chicken broth and cream.
Stir and cook until the sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the mustard.
Return the chicken to the skillet, cover and heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with hot cooked rice.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Use this as frosting for cake.
Be sure and refrigerate cake.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add all ingredients to cake mix. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes in a tube pan.
(I use lemon or orange Jell-O.)
This cake ages well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and peanut butter.
Bring to a boil and boil about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix corn flakes into mixture as best you can.
Let cool some and butter your hands real good before you make balls.
Form into any size ball.
Sticks together better as it cools.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove from pan.
Fry onion and pepper in bacon fat until soft.
In large pot or casserole, combine lima beans, onion, pepper, chili sauce and sugar.
Add bacon.
Mix well and bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all in blender until ice is crushed.

title: bread machine cardamom julbrod
directions: Place milk, butter, egg, sugar, salt, cardamom, flour and yeast into bread machine in order suggested by manufacturer's directions.
For white or raisin bread, adding raisins, citron and almonds at the beep.
Makes 1 1/2 pound loaf.

title: cookies
directions: Mix cake mix with margarine and egg.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Mixture will be very thick.
May have to mix with hands. Chill dough for 1 hour before baking.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: crab cakes
directions: In one bowl mix crab meat and crackers.
In another bowl, mix all other ingredients and pour over crab meat.
Stir and form into cakes.
Sprinkle top and bottom of cakes with batter mix.
Fry quickly until golden brown.

title: oatmeal jelly delights
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 1/2 in greased pan. Pat well and spread with 1 1/2 cups jam.
Put remainder on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good with strawberry rhubarb or raspberry jam.

title: fruit cake candy
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Press mixture into 2 small wax paper lined loaf pans.
Let stand several hours.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°.
Cool and store in freezer, if not served right away.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Prepare shells according to package directions for salad use. Combine all ingredients except lettuce.
Chill.
Just before serving, toss salad with lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy mexican nut mix
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In small bowl, toss together shredded wheat and nuts; set aside. In small bowl, place the egg whites, honey, chili powder, thyme, salt and cayenne; stir vigorously with a fork until completely blended. Pour over the nut mixture and toss continuously for about 2 minutes, to distribute the flavors and coat the cereal and nuts evenly. Transfer the mixture to a baking pan and bake for about 20 minutes, stirring once or twice, until the mixture has browned lightly. Cool to room temperature. Store in airtight container. Makes about 4 quarts.

title: zucchini or pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Mix together zucchini or pumpkin with soda, sugar, shortening or butter and beaten egg.
Sift in flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir to blend.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.

title: s'mores on a stick(snack)
directions: Place the package of marshmallows in the freezer for 10-15 minutes.
Melt the chocolate chips in the microwave until they are nice and creamy.
Please graham crackers in a zip-lock bag and crush until fine with a rolling pin. Now take out your marshmallows.
Place a stick in a marshmallow and dip it in the chocolate and cover it completely.
Now roll it in the graham cracker crumb.
Continue until the marshmallows are gone.
Wrap in lollipop papers and tie with a bow.

title: herb butter(great with broiled or baked fish and chicken.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a jar for storage.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In saucepan, blend sugar, vinegar and peppers.
Bring to a hard boil; boil 3 minutes.
Add liquid pectin; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Cool 6 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: sauteed zucchini
directions: Saute sliced zucchini in butter until soft.
Sprinkle top with parmesan cheese and serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together; store in 1 gallon container. To serve, fill cup 1/3 cup of mixture (approximately) and add hot water.

title: martha's muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Mix other ingredients in separate bowl.
With dry mixture add 1/2 cup milk and first mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Heat margarine and marshmallows.
Add and mix cherries, raisins, dates, pecans and graham crackers.
Set in refrigerator after shaping into loaf.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chewy cake
directions: Beat one egg and butter.
Add cake mix, mixing until crumbly. Add coconut and nuts.
Pat mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch prepared pan.
Beat together softened cream cheese, remaining two eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: "sand tarts"
directions: Roll in small oblong balls and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Take out and roll in powdered sugar.

title: ambrosia spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat until smooth.
Serve with breads, muffins or fruit.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields about 2 cups of spread.

title: party dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, Cheez Whiz and chicken spread.
Add dressing as desired for consistency.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: muenster cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly and add milk and flour. Alternately, add cheese, meat and spices.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Do not mix ahead of time.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: nannie's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients well with electric beaters; pour into casserole dish.
Bake in 325° oven for about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle top with marshmallows and return to oven until melted and lightly browned.

title: make-ahead pork chop casserole
directions: Saute pork chops in skillet until brown.
Place rice in casserole.
Layer pork chops and vegetables over rice; pour bouillon over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until pork chops are tender, adding water if necessary.

title: amazing custard pie or coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add 1 cup coconut if desired for coconut pie.

title: homemade amaretto liqueur
directions: Use inexpensive vodka and brandy. Combine water and sugar. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into tightly covered bottles.
Makes 6+ cups. Serve with cola and ice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix with electric mixer the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
On low speed, blend in eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to cheese mixture.
Blend until smooth. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Serves 12.

title: baked italian potatoes
directions: Slice
potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through. Place in baking dish and fan slices slightly.
Pour salad dressing over potatoes.
Cover dish with saran wrap and microwave on high for 5 minutes.
Rotate potatoes, cover and cook on high for 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then microwave on high for another 4-6 minutes or until potatoes are soft when tested with a fork.

title: green rice
directions: Thaw broccoli. Mix soup, water, salt and pepper. Separate (break) broccoli into mixture.

title: orange chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix dressing, juice and seasonings in a large bowl.
Ad remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Refrigerate before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: betty's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons of sugar in 1 cup of warm water.
Stir it up.
Put in small pot and let it raise 5 minutes or so.

title: grandma whitlatch's chinese fried rice
directions: Fry ham, pepper and onion together, then stir in bean sprouts, along with rice.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: deer jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients; add meat and soak overnight.
Take meat out and place on towels and press dry.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 200° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn meat and bake another 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and place on towels and press dry.

title: raisin cupcakes
directions: Boil raisins in 2 cups water for 20 minutes; set aside to cool.
Sift dry ingredients, except sugar.
Mix sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and extracts.
Drain raisin water; add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes.

title: caramel oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add oats and chocolate chips. Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: christmas fettuccini
directions: Cook the pasta in boiling water.
Add a dash of salt for taste.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Mix with sweet milk until batter is stiff.
With a teaspoon, drop into hot grease until brown.
Drain and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust; bake in preheated oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: beef roast
directions: Place roast in pan. Sprinkle soup mix on roast. Mix mushroom soup with water and pour over roast. Cover and bake at 300° until done.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook together first 5 ingredients until thickened.
Add cooked beets and 2 tablespoons margarine.

title: pear honey
directions: Grate the rind of orange.
Peel and core all fruit.
Run all fruit (pears, apples and orange) through a blender until it is of applesauce consistency.
The add grated orange rind.
Cook to near soft ball stage, then can.
Yields approximately 2 pints.

title: rita's chicken
directions: Batter the chicken in a mixture of Bisquick mix and yellow corn meal and brown quickly in some vegetable oil.
Remove chicken and place in a Pyrex baking dish.
Mix in a mixing bowl the Russian dressing, apricot preserves and dry onion soup mix.
Pour over the chicken and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: good hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate over night.

title: coconut refrigerator cake
directions: Make a two or three layer cake as directed on the package. If you make a 2 layer cake, split each one.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Place chicken in a pan and salt chicken.
Melt butter and spoon over each piece.
Cook at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Bake in greased and floured loaf or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cookie bars
directions: Place melted butter in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter and mix together.
Press mixture into pan.
Pour milk over crumbs and top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken crunchy
directions: Mix ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Stir.
Grate Mozzarella cheese on top.
Crumble potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° until barely hot.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs, applesauce and pineapple.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices and add to first mixture.
Add raisins, nuts, cherries and vanilla.
Bake in large greased and floured tube pan in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 4 tablespoons cold water, then add to boiling water, sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice and boil. Put in refrigerator until jelled.
Remove brown from cake; break up into little pieces in glass oblong dish (11 x 13-inch).
After gelatine mixture is jelled, add to Cool Whip and pineapple, then add to cake and blend well with spatula.
Put coconut on top and refrigerate.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Heat grease, sugar and tomatoes.
Add bread chunks and simmer until bread
"dissolves."

title: easy cinnamon-pecan rolls
directions: Combine pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Separate rolls at perforations and spray one side with cooking spray or brush with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture and roll according to package directions.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: soft brown sugar cookies
directions: Blend together sugar, egg, butter, and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: taco bean dip
directions: In 9-inch pie plate, spread cream cheese, then a layer of beans, then chili.
Top with salsa, then sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cook in microwave about 5 minutes until heated through. Serve with taco chips.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops.
Dice potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain potatoes.
Pour about 1/2 of soup in casserole dish; add potatoes, then pork chops and the remainder of soup.
Put in oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: cincinnati empress chili
directions: Mix all together and cook 6 hours over low heat in heavy pan (don't brown beef).
Skim fat off top before serving.
Can be eaten as is or served as 4 or 5-way chili.
Cook and drain spaghetti; put on plate, top with chili.
Add beans, chopped onions and grated cheese as desired (remove bay leaf).
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: sour cream dressing for baked potatoes
directions: Mix well and pour over hot baked potatoes.

title: creamy autumn potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 1-quart casserole dish.
In 1-quart saucepan, saute in butter over medium heat, chopped onions and garlic until tender.
Stir in undiluted soup and cream cheese cubes.
Cook and stir constantly until smooth and hot.
In casserole, alternately layer potatoes and hot cream cheese sauce ending with a sauce layer.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Yield:
4 to 5 servings.

title: baked spam
directions: Place Spam in shallow baking dish; score top with knife and stud with cloves.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then spread with paste mixed of sugar, mustard, vinegar and water.
Bake 15 minutes longer, basting every 5 minutes with Spam juices.
Slice and serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, cheese, onion, and chicken soup together. Melt margarine. Mix 2 Tbsp. with rice krispies. Add remaining margarine to potato mixture. Put in a 3 qt. casserole dish. Top with rice krispies. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Pour into unbaked shell.

title: hot buttered rum sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; add to butter while stirring.
Add milk, egg and rum.
Cook until smooth and glossy.
Serve over pound cake, bread pudding or ice cream.

title: fruit surprise
directions: Combine juices from oranges and pineapple with Jell-O pudding. Cook until thickens and turns clear.
Fold in fruit.
Top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: salmon pie
directions: Bone and drain salmon.
Add to white sauce and drained peas. Place in baking dish and top with mashed potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Brown in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: green chile dip
directions: Peel chile, remove stems and seeds and chop fine.
Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Blend cheese and chile.
Serve with tostados, potato chips, crackers, celery or carrot sticks or corn chips.
Good as a dip, fine as a spread.

title: sandy's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and water mixture and the buttermilk.
Roll out and cut into biscuits. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
They may be frozen and popped into a hot oven just before serving.

title: master mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times into large bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Store in airtight container at room temperature.
Yields 13 cups mix.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Cook noodles until al dente, drain and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a big skillet and saute onion, garlic, tomatoes and mushrooms.
When onion is translucent, add herbs and spinach, stirring until spinach wilts.
Simmer.
Reserving 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, in a large bowl combine cheeses and eggs.
Pour vegetables into cheese mixture and mix thoroughly.
Layer noodles alternately with vegetable-cheese mixture in an 8 x 13-inch pan. Top with reserved cheese and more Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli souffle squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spread crescent rolls out on cookie sheet, pinch seams together. Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain thoroughly. In a large bowl combine broccoli, eggs, mayonnaise, soup, onion,
5 ounces cheese, tabasco sauce and salt. Mix well. Spread evenly over crescent rolls, top with remaining cheese. Bake 20-30 minutes until golden brown. Serve immediately or cool slightly.

title: pickled beets
directions: Add the
sugar, vinegar and pickling spices to the liquid. Bring to a boil and put in beets. Bring to another boil and set off heat.

title: wiggins barbecue chicken
directions: Put cut up chicken into pot.
Put all other ingredients into pot, then put enough water in to almost cover chicken.
Bring to boil and cook until almost done.
Then put on grill to finish cooking.
Can bake in oven instead of putting on grill.
Good chicken!

title: moose mario
directions: Blend vinegar and water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add carrots, garlic, parsley, cloves and 1 onion; allow to cool. Put moose in this mixture; let marinate for 24 hours in a cool place.
Take moose out of mixture.
Dry it with paper towels; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Rub in flour.
Put 4 slices of bacon over moose.
Add white onions and place in baking dish. Brown on both sides in hot oven about 30 minutes.
Add all vegetables in which moose marinated; add a little of the liquid. Lower heat to moderate oven.
Baste occasionally with liquid, using enough to make a gravy.
Roast 1 1/2 hours or until tender, then add sherry.
Simmer slowly for 10 more minutes.

title: minestrone soup(yield: 6 servings)
directions: Spray a 6-quart slow cooker with vegetable oil cooking spray. Heat the olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook until soft, about 7 to 8 minutes. Add the Italian seasoning, tomatoes, carrots, celery and zucchini and cook for 5 minutes. Place the cooked vegetable mixture in the slow cooker. Add the string beans, cabbage, potatoes, salt, pepper and water. Stir to combine. Cover and cook on low for 8 hours. Add the kidney beans and pasta 20 minutes before serving. Cook until the pasta is tender. Stir in the cheese and serve immediately.

title: peanut bars
directions: Beat egg yolks, salt, vanilla and sugar about 5 minutes.
Sift flour once with baking powder; add to egg mixture, alternating with cold water, beating at "blend" speed to mix smooth after each addition.
Beat egg whites until they hold stiff peaks, but are not dry.
Gently fold in with rubber spatula the egg whites in batter. Pour into 9 x 13 cake pan lined with wax paper; do not grease or flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut in pieces your choice of size, approximately 1 x 2 1/2-inches.
Frost with Peanut Bar Frosting.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan.
Add chopped pepper and onions; simmer until soft.
Drain off grease.
Add Ortego seasoning sauce. Line a square cake pan with crunched Doritos.
Add ground beef. Sprinkle on top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Microwave Cheez Whiz until soft and pour over top.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix first four ingredients well with mixer and pour into freezer can.
Finish filling with milk.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients except bread and refrigerate overnight. Carve out inside of rye bread and cut into serving pieces.
Fill the bread cavity with the spinach mixture when you are ready to serve.
Use the bread cubes to dip into the mix.

title: summer cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots, radishes and pickles.
Chop tomato, scallions (plus tops), celery and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients.
Let set 1 hour before serving.
Cover.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans; set aside. In medium bowl, stir thawed strawberries, eggs and oil. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nuts. Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until blended. Pour into pans. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Yield: 2 loaves.

title: meat roll
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion, salt, pepper, garlic powder, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.

Brown mixture in large skillet. Continue to cook until onion is tender; drain and discard fat. Blend baking mix and milk to soft dough; turn onto lightly floured surface and roll into 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cover with meat mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Place on greased baking sheet, seam side down.
Slash top several times with knife.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter and powdered sugar. Add the vanilla and water.
Add flour and mix well.
Add pecans and make into rolls 1 1/2-inches long and about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Roll in powdered sugar when slightly cooled.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package; rinse.
In a medium pot, melt butter.
Blend in milk and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour over macaroni; stir until blended.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients according to cake box directions and divide batter in half.
To one half, add the brown sugar, chopped nuts and Kahlua.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix
first
ingredients.
Sift the next 4 and add to the first
mixture.
Fold
in pecans and apples last.
Mix by hand
as batter
is
very stiff.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan
for 1 hour or 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: almond french toast
directions: Process almonds, honey and cinnamon in a blender.
Add evaporated milk to thin.
Use this as sandwich filling on bread slices.
Brush both sides with melted butter.
Mix remaining butter, eggs, vanilla and almond extract.
Dip sandwiches in egg batter like French toast.
Broil about 3 minutes; turn and broil second side.
Freeze or serve immediately with syrup.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken in olive oil. Then shred it. Place all ingredients in a pan and cook till noodles are done. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: butterscotch shortbread cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix shortening and sugars throughly. Measure flour by dipping method or sifting.
Mix flour and salt; stir in.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll out to 1/4-inch on floured board. Cut in desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased sheet 20 to 25 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour and Crisco with a fork and add milk.
Stir until creamy.
Roll out on floured paper.
Cut and place on greased pan. Bake at 450° until done.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let stand 2 hours. Add remaining ingredients (do not heat).
Mix well.
Put into jars and refrigerate.
Will keep for months.

title: oven style swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Place in a deep baking dish.
Top with onion and mushrooms.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Cook 15 minutes longer, uncovered.
Baste occasionally.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Place the following in pan:
mustard, vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, salt, pepper and pickling spice bag.
Bring to boil and add cabbage, onions and pimento.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Mix 1 cup flour with enough water to form paste; slowly stir into relish mixture.
Cook for few minutes longer.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: baked onion chicken
directions: With rolling pin, crush soup mix in pouch.
On waxed paper, combine soup mix, bread crumbs and black pepper.
In
shallow dish, beat together egg and water.
Dip chicken into egg mixture. Coat with crumb mixture.
On baking sheet, arrange chicken. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cook time: 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix using 1/2 of the dried beef.
Use remainder of beef to roll the ball in.
Chill, slice and serve.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in boiling water; cool.
Add to juices; chill.

title: chicken of the gods
directions: Marinate chicken in salt, egg, sherry and soy sauce for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut up marinated chicken into large pieces and dip in flour.
Brown in oil and cook until done.
Melt butter over medium heat and blend in cornstarch.
Bring stock to boil and stir rapidly while adding butter and cornstarch mixture.
Reduce heat and add cream, seasonings and mushrooms.
Cut up cooked chicken into smaller strips.
Cover with cream sauce and sprinkle sesame seeds on top for garnish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: onion steak and potatoes
directions: In
large
skillet, brown steak in oil.
Stir in water, soup mix,
salt,
pepper
and potatoes.
Heat to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.
Add green beans, cover and cook 10 minutes.
Remove meat and vegetables to platter.
Blend
water and flour.
Stir into hot liquid in skillet and stir until thickened.
Serve over meat and vegetables.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 3 minutes.
Put in jars.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and vinegar.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add butter and beets.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on medium until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Serve with:
1/2 cup each:
chopped cukes and green peppers/onions and 1 cup seasoned croutons.
Makes 8 appetizer servings (1/2 cup each).
Contains 65 calories per serving.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown beef.
Add soup and seasonings.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Cook noodles.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, for 55 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot totty
directions: In a saucepan, heat cranberry juice cocktail just to boiling. Pour into an 8 ounce mug, stir in brandy.
Garnish with a cinnamon stick.
Yields 1 serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans
well.
Roll into ball and store in an airtight container overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, flour and 1/2 of thawed strawberries. Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup hot water (cool before adding).
Add oil, vanilla and eggs one at a time.
This takes a large Pyrex and a small Pyrex pan (9 x 13-inch and 4 x 8-inch).
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Frost with 1 pound powdered sugar mixed with remaining 1/2 strawberries.
Make holes in cake with fork or ice pick to allow icing to penetrate.

title: debbie's pasta salad
directions: Add any vegetable that looks good.

title: peschealla piemontepe(piedmontese stuffed peaches)
directions: Wash 6 peaches, dry and cut in half.
Remove stems. Scoop out a little of the peach flesh into middle and put into bowl.
Mash to a puree.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons of butter, egg yolk and macaroons to puree.
Mix well and fill each peach half with some of the mixture, piling it up in the middle.
Arrange the peach halves in a ovenproof dish and dot with the remaining butter. Bake in a moderate 375° oven for about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Keep cream cheese at room temperature.
Put cream cheese, sugar and eggs in a bowl; blend until very creamy.
Place a vanilla wafer with round part facing up.
Spoon 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture on top of each vanilla wafer.
Put in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
May put cherry on top.

title: corn 'n sausage chowder
directions: Heat all ingredients in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently until hot.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring by hand until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not use electric mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Finally, add bananas.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and place in bowl.
Shred onion and pepper and place on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle sugar over the top; do not stir.
Bring to boil the oil, vinegar, celery seed, mustard and salt.
Pour over cabbage mixture while hot.
Cover and refrigerate without stirring for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.
Will keep crisp for a week if refrigerated.

title: chef salad sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; mix with mixer until all ingredients are well mixed.
Makes 1 quart dressing.

title: shortcut fettucini alfredo
directions: Return noodles to pan after drained.
Add margarine, cream, salt and pepper.
Add cheese.
Add egg at room temperature.
Cook over low flame for 1 minute.
To this you may add any vegetable, fresh or frozen (carrots, peas, broccoli, etc.).

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. In a med. sized mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Beat in sweetened condensed milk. Add lemon juice and vanilla; mix well. Pour filling into crust. Chill several hours and then top with cherry pie filling.

title: melon salad
directions: Make the dressing: Grate the lime zest in a bowl. Stir together the lime zest, lime juice, tangerine juice and the coriander or vanilla. Cut each melon half into 1-inch wide wedges; remove the rind. Cut the melon wedges crosswise. Add the melon to the dressing, then add the grapes. Toss gently to combine. Cover bowl loosely with plastic wrap and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until serving. If possible, refrigerate until well chilled, about 2 hours.

title: glazed sausage bites
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil in a skillet.
Add sausages to mixture.
Simmer until sausages are cooked and glazed.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Combine all ingredients and bake in buttered bread pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until done.
Cool 15 minutes before turning out if Bundt pan is used.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Combine chicken, Pace thick and chunky salsa, onion and cumin; mix well.
Heat about 1/2 inch oil in small skillet until hot, but not smoking.
Quickly fry each tortilla in oil to soften, about 2 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Peel the sweet potatoes and cut into small chunks; boil until done and mash. Add the butter and honey and then roll into small balls. Roll them into coconut and place into the oven until slightly browned; remove and serve hot.

title: potato bread
directions: Mix together potatoes, water, sugar and yeast.
Let rise in warm place overnight.
In the morning, add melted butter, eggs and flour to make a very soft dough.
Form into balls the size of walnuts by rolling dough in hands.
Keep hands well buttered to prevent sticking.
Place close together in a well-greased shallow pan.
Place in oven at 200° for just 1 minute, just enough to warm oven.
Let rise 2 hours, then bake 2 hours and 15 minutes at 400°.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Put tomatoes and onion in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add margarine, sugar, salt and oregano.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add bread.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: julia's biscuits
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add the milk.
Make into biscuits.
Bake at 450° to 475° until done.

title: cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over oleo.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs.
Top with all the chips.
Press down.
Bake 1/2 hour.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375°
about 40 minutes or until set.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk and beaten eggs.
Cook until very thick, about 10 minutes.
Pour a thin covering of mixture over baked pie shell.
Place strawberries on top and add remaining mixture.
Top with whipped cream.

title: carrot nut loaf
directions: Add small amount of milk to flour; blend until smooth. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in loaf or 30 minutes in muffin tins.
Serves 8.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over the Bran Buds and let stand.
Combine the other ingredients.
Add Bran Buds and water.
Add raisins. Bake at 400° in miniature muffin pans for 12 to 15 minutes or when springs back when touched.
Will keep 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pineapple-date salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple liquid and cream together.
Add pineapple, nuts and dates.
Mix together.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Freeze in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Serve frozen.

title: cheese whiz and rice
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and then mix with other items.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: jette's mother's coffeecake
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly, then beat in milk and yeast mixture.
In a large bowl or food processor, combine 3 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until particles are fine.
Stir in yeast mixture and lemon peel.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Stir in about 1/4 cup flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured board and knead (adding flour only if necessary to prevent sticking) until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl, cover tightly and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
After removing from refrigerator, let stand at room temperature to warm (or press with hands to warm and soften). Roll into a 20 x 16-inch rectangle.
Stir together egg whites, nuts and remaining cup of sugar.
Spread on dough.
Starting at lengthwise edge nearest you, roll as for jelly roll.
Grease Bundt pan, then carefully lift roll and place, seam side up, in prepared pan, adjusting to fit and overlapping ends to join.
Cover and let stand 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a rich golden brown.
(Start to check after 30 minutes and when top begins to turn golden, cover loosely with foil for remainder of baking time.)
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then gently loosen at edges and around center tube.
Turn out on wire rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, sifted.
Makes 18 slices.
This sounds time-consuming to prepare, but it is very easy and very delicious.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over zucchini and onions; let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Bring combined mixture to a boil, then simmer 3 minutes.
Continue simmering while quickly packing one clean, hot jar at a time. Fill to within 1/2-inch of top, making sure vinegar solution covers vegetables.
Cap each jar at once.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: scallops tetrazzini
directions: Heat oil
in
3 quart nonstick saucepan with the onion, garlic and
pepper.
Saute
minutes.
Add flour and seasonings;
stir to
combine.
Add milk, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, celery, green pepper, mushrooms and cheese and stir over medium heat until
sauce
coats
the spoon.
Remove bay leaf. Combine half the
sauce with the cooked linguini and place in the bottom
of
a 3
quart
shallow
casserole dish.
Add the scallops to the remaining sauce and pour over pasta.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan
cheese
and bake in preheated 350° oven for 25
to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.
A rich but very heart-smart dish.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in big bowl.
Make into small balls. Put cornflakes on waxed paper.
Roll balls into cornflakes.
Eat, then clean up.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Scramble eggs.
Don't overcook. Fry sausage (scrambled) and drain.
Mix eggs and sausage in a 7 x 11-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until al dente.
Drain and spread out in large bowl. Coat with 2 tablespoons olive oil.
When cool, sprinkle with basil, oregano, Mozzarella, tomato and olives.
Mix garlic with remaining olive oil and add to salad.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste and Asagio or other good, freshly grated Parmesan or Romano cheese. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk, cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Cool and mix in vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into two baked pie crusts.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: beets and orange
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add butter. Blend over low heat.
Slowly stir in orange juice.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens and is smooth.
Pour over beets.
Garnish with slices of mandarin oranges.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour into a skillet.
Mix together. Slowly add butter and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.

title: lasagna
directions: Pour small amount of sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with 3 lasagna noodles.
Spread 1/2 cheese mixture, then 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat; top with noodles and rest of sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 20 minutes more.
Remove from oven and let stand 15 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: maple syrup pudding
directions: Heat maple syrup to boiling point.
Place in buttered 1 to 2-quart size round baking dish.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Add the eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Moisten with sufficient milk to make a batter.
Pour batter onto boiling maple syrup and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
When slightly cooled, turn upside down onto plate and decorate with pecan halves.
Top with whipped cream, decorated with pecan halves.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Finish filling with homogenized milk.

title: banana bars
directions: Combine butter and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add buttermilk and bananas; mix well.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla.
Pour into pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: swiss ham pie
directions: Bake pastry shell in 450° oven for 7 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; spoon this mixture in the middle of the tortillas and roll up and save 1/2 mixture and spread over the top.
Sprinkle with cheese and black olives.
Bake at 350 for 30-45 minutes and serve with sour cream.

title: italian sausage lasagne
directions: Cook and stir sausage, onion and garlic in 10-inch skillet until sausage is brown; drain.
Stir in 2 tablespoons parsley, the sugar, basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, the tomatoes and tomato sauce; break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until slightly thickened, about 45 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread breasts flat; fold ham and cheese to fit on top.
Fold over; fasten with toothpicks.
On waxed paper, mix flour and paprika; coat chicken.
In hot butter, cook chicken until brown on all sides.
Add wine and bouillon.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, or until fork-tender.
Remove toothpicks.

title: face paint (white)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Put cold cream or lotion on, then put paint in desired area.
Use peanut butter or coconut for warts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with butter.
Take 1/2 out of pan and spread rest on bottom of pan.
Next, place deboned chicken on mixture.
Mix up mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and 2 1/2 cups broth together.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Put remaining stuffing on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salt water for about 7 minutes. Drain.
Mix eggs, pickles, pepper and onion.
Add mayonnaise and seasonings.
Combine with macaroni.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: chocolate surprise bars
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and baking soda in a small bowl; mix and cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and cocoa.
Add flour alternately with date mixture and beat well.
Spread into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Dust immediately with powdered sugar when removed from oven.

title: creamed corn
directions: Note:
I use evaporated milk or a little cream if I don't have whole milk.

title: apple, peach or pear crisp(so easy, so good)
directions: Mix fruit with enough sugar to sweeten slightly.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
In a pan, melt margarine.
Remove from heat. Add flour, oatmeal, sugar and cinnamon.
Stir until crumbly. Sprinkle over fruit.
Top with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or cheese if desired.

title: steamed cabbage supreme
directions: Cook cabbage in a small amount of water and salt, pepper and sugar to taste; better a little sweet.
Cook until crisp-tender. Melt margarine.
Stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Stir this into the cabbage.
Add enough milk to make it creamy.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: "crabbies"(crabmeat appetizers)
directions: Put English muffins in freezer for 10 minutes.
Mix first four ingredients.
Add crabmeat.
Spread mix on muffins and put in freezer until partially frozen; then cut into 6's or 8's.
Can be thoroughly frozen on cookie sheet and stored in plastic bag to be used when you wish.
Just take out 15 minutes before heating in a regular 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large pot over high heat, cook ground beef and onion until pan juices evaporate and beef is brown.
Add tomatoes and their liquid and the next seven ingredients.
Heat mixture to boiling, stirring to break up the tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer thirty minutes, stirring mixture occasionally. Discard the bay leaf.
Tilt pan and spoon off any fat which accumulates on top of the sauce.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on the package and drain well in colander.
In
a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange half of the drained lasagna noodles, overlapping to fit.

title: vegetable dip(low calorie, no fat)
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate.

title: three bean turkey soup
directions: Sort, wash and place beans in water 2 inches above beans.
Let soak overnight.
Drain well.
Combine beans and water in kettle. Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Drain beans, reserving 3 cups water.
Transfer 1/3 cup beans to small bowl; mash with fork to make a paste.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Stir together oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and green tomatoes. Sift together remaining ingredients (cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg). Add dry ingredients; then pour batter into 2 oiled loaf pans.
(I like to line my pans with waxed paper.)
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour (other ingredients can be used, 1 1/2 cups green tomatoes, 1/2 cup grated apple or 1/2 cup crushed pineapple).

title: rice pie
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Pat mixture into bottom and sides of greased 10-inch pie plate.
Combine rice with remaining tomato sauce and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Spoon into meat shell.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake slowly for 10 more minutes.

title: special torte
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually with vanilla.
Beat until very thick, then add broken saltine crackers and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When cooled, top with a layer of whipped topping and then a layer of pie filling.

title: taco pie dip
directions: Make layers in order given.
Serve with tostado chips, etc. Cover with foil and store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: Boil pasta; drain well and put in pot.
Add half and half cream and Parmesan cheese, a little at a time.
Stir constantly. Add broccoli and cooked shrimp; heat thoroughly and serve.

title: cheese on toast with tomato soup
directions: Heat soup; put aside.
Toast the bread.
Arrange bread on cookie sheet and top with cheese slices.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.
Spoon soup on top and enjoy.
This is a great quick kids lunch.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serve with party crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix jello in 3/4 cup hot water.
Add juice from fruit cocktail.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: lemon oat bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, whisk together the condensed milk and lemon juice until blended; stir in lemon rind.
Reserve.
In medium bowl, beat butter and brown sugar with wooden spoon.
Sprinkle with flour and baking powder and stir until blended.
Stir in oats.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Spread half of the flour-oat mixture in pan, patting it down.
Spread lemon mixture over top.
Sprinkle with remaining flour-oat mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Chill before cutting into bars.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together well.
Put in pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and boil over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add pecans.
Place 12 whole graham crackers in 2 (9 x 12-inch) pans.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars.

title: wild goose or duck(tennessee)
directions: Boil goose or duck in seasoned water until tender.
Remove meat from bone.
Add mixture to Pepper Oriental and gravy.
Makes a pretty dish also.

title: fruited pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and sugar together until creamy. Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in pumpkin and bananas.
Sift flour with soda, salt and spices.
Mix into creamed mixture just until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Put into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool for about 5 minutes and turn out onto rack to completely cool.

title: carol's fat free pudding dessert
directions: Prepare 1 large box of instant sugar free, fat free pudding mix with 1 1/2 cups fat free milk.
Add 1 cup Lite Cool Whip and 1 small tube fat free cream cheese and mix well.
Gently fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.

title: delicatessen reuben
directions: Cover toast with sauerkraut, meat, cheese and onion.
Place under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is melted. Top with avocado slices and dressing.
Serve open-style with pickle garnish.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add cocoa and flour to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.
Spread marshmallows evenly over top of cake.
Return cake to oven for 5 minutes.
Then frost with Mississippi Mud Frosting.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and salt.
Add beaten egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Scrape batter into an ungreased 12 x 17 jelly roll pan and pat out evenly.
Baked on the lowest shelf of oven, 15-20 minutes at 350 F.
Remove from oven and while still hot, lay squares of Hershey bars on top.
Spread the chocolate with spatula to cover and sprinkle with topping (pecans, oil and salt mixed together).
Put back in the oven for 5 minutes at 350 F.
Cut into squares.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add hamburger to other ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and press or squeeze spinach until all water is removed. Mix all ingredients and chill.

This can be served with vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, radishes, celery, carrots); crackers or brown bread, sliced; or round brown bread that has been hollowed out and used as a container with remaining bread sliced and alternated with vegetables.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Put in crock-pot and add cheese chunks and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor until finely chopped.
Chill and serve.

title: summertime fruit cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch pan with some margarine, pour in fruit mixture.
Spread cake mix over the fruit evenly.
Cut the rest of margarine in small slices and drop over the cake mix.
Sprinkle the pecans over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon fluff cake
directions: On top, put brown sugar, cinnamon and dot good with butter. Use 9 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Combine celery, onion, butter and water in saucepan and bring to boil. Add to cornbread mixture.
Stir in broth, oil and eggs and mix well.
Pour into grease baking dish and bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger mini muffins
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is done; drain. In a bowl, combine the flour and sugar. In another bowl, combine the ketchup, milk, butter, eggs and mustard; stir into the dry ingredients until moistened. Fold in the beef mixture and cheese. Fill greased miniature muffin cups three-fourths full. Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn with sugar, flour and salt mixture.
Add beaten egg along with milk and butter.
Pour into greased casserole and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together; store in closed container.
Place 2 heaping tablespoonfuls in one cup hot water; stir well.

title: tuna romanoff
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and next 3 ingredients; saute for 6 minutes or until tender.

title: chili lousiana style
directions: Cook meat until gray.
Blend (in blender) garlic, jalapeno peppers, tomatoes, flour, chili powder.
Mix all this with meat. Saute onions and bell pepper with 2 tablespoons cooking oil. Add this and beans with above. Cook slowly 1 & 1/2 hours. Add water for desired thickness. Stir often.
Makes approximately 15 pints.

title: quick peach pastry
directions: Unroll rolls.
Pat into bottom of a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread with jam. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Reduce heat to 325°.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour evenly over rolls. Return to oven. Bake 5 to 6 minutes. When cool, sprinkle with cinnamon sugar (can make ahead and refrigerate).

title: hilda's fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and sugar. Add egg and fruit cocktail. Mix together and pour into greased 7 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle top of cake with brown sugar and walnut meats. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Serve when cold with whipped cream and Cool Whip.

title: basil parmesan quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Combine flour, baking powder, salt, Parmesan and basil in mixing bowl.
Form a well in the center and add eggs, milk and butter. Mix just until moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Spread into pan and bake 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out dry.
Cool before slicing.

title: cherry salad(congealed)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in jello until dissolved.
Add about 1/2 cups chopped pecans, if desired.
Put in jello mold or 8 x 8 pyrex dish.
Chill until set.
Very good compliment to deer soup.
Serves 9. (Easily doubled or tripled for a big deer soup feast.)

title: pecan chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve over lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: scampi-shrimp
directions: In a large skillet, put all ingredients except shrimp and rice. Stir over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add shrimp; stir until shrimp are pink.
Serve with rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread by package directions.
Crumble cornbread and mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: fresh peach pie(this pie is a peach.)
directions: In a saucepan, boil sugar, cornstarch, salt and water for 1 minute, stirring gently.
Let cool.
Place in a bowl and mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: 10 day amish cinnamon bread
directions: Day One:
Mix listed ingredients or receive starter.

title: pastel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Divide batter into 2 bowls.
Add lime Jell-O to 1 bowl and lemon Jell-O to another.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour each into separate wax-paper-lined, greased, and floured 9 inch round cake pan.
Bake 28-30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on wire racks.
Place lime cake layer on serving platter and layer with one bowl Cool Whip.
Top with lemon cake layer.
Frost cake with remaining Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: almond poppy seed bread(no fat!)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix with electric mixer for about 2 minutes.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add oleo and blend.
Add beaten egg. Combine soda with buttermilk; add to mixture.
Stir in extract. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain off grease.
Put in casserole dish; add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until rice is tender, about 1 hour.

title: baked quail with burgundy wine
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll quail in mixture and brown in hot oil.
Place birds on rack in roasting pan.
Add water for steam.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add red wine and continue baking for another half hour or until tender.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: You will need a large skillet, large crock-pot and microwave oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs and pumpkin all together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour in greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until done.

title: no-rise rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix oil and slightly beaten egg into the yeast mixture.
Add flour last. Mix together, using low speed on mixer.
Place in tightly covered container and store in refrigerator.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and salt until thick and clear. Add Jell-O.
Stir until cool.
Add the sliced strawberries.
Pour into a baked pie shell and place in the refrigerator until firm. Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream before serving.

title: potato "tater" soup
directions: Dice potatoes into a large saucepan.
Cover with water.
Add chopped onion and celery.
Boil until almost soft, but not completely.
Thicken with cornstarch or flour, diluted with 1/2 cup warm water.
Return to a simmering boil.
Add milk and reduce heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Goes great with hot cornbread.)

title: brownies
directions: Mix the oleo, water and cocoa; bring to a boil, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes in greased pan.

title: dream frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add milk, then butter.
Bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Cool in water.
Beat.
Frost.

title: sweet sour carrots
directions: Peel, slice, cook and drain carrots; set aside.
Mix in saucepan the sugar, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Add vinegar, oil, tomato soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes; pour over carrots.
Add chopped onion and pepper.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onion and cook 10 more minutes. Add tomato sauce, catsup, salt and pepper to taste. Cook 5 minutes.

title: my mother's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cover with 1 pint Hellmann's mayonnaise (no salad dressing) and let sit in refrigerator, covered with Saran Wrap, 24 hours. Stir just before serving.

title: oven stew
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole.
Stir to mix.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: philadelphia cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Add cream cheese while hot. Cream cheese will not entirely dissolve. When beginning to thicken, add whipped cream, nuts, pineapple, pimentos and lemon juice. Let set until firm in refrigerator.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil butter and sugar 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda and mix well.
Pour all this over popped popcorn.
Add nuts, if desired.
Put in cake pan in 250° oven for one hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: mama's old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Cut cooked potatoes in cubes.
Combine all ingredients and serve warm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine flour, 1 1/3 cups sugar and salt in a heavy saucepan. Beat egg yolks.
Combine egg yolks and milk, mixing well.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, starch and cocoa; add eggs and melted butter, milk, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 400° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Prepare vanilla instant pudding and cold milk until almost thick.
Fold in whipped topping until mixture thickens.
Make a layer of whole graham crackers in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers. Top with remaining pudding mix, spreading evenly.
Place a layer of crackers on top.
Chill 1 hour.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: zucchini and onions with mozzarella
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato and cheese.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is crisply tender (7 to 10 minutes). Add tomato wedges; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot and leek soup
directions: Cook carrots and leeks (washed and peeled) in chicken broth about 25 minutes or until it is soft.
Blend in blender with a handful of parsley.
Serve hot.

title: kids favorite fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except whipped topping. Mix lightly. Gently fold in whipped topping.
Cover and chill until served.
Spoon salad onto lettuce-lined plates and garnish with additional maraschino cherries, if desired.
Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Place sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, pepper and carrot. Let stand 2 hours.
Pour in containers and freeze.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Place in saucepan all ingredients except walnuts.
Stir and boil constantly for 3 minutes.
Fold in nuts and stir until well coated and stringy.
Break apart with fork.
Store covered.

title: cenci (wandi)
directions: Into a large bowl, measure flour.
In medium bowl, beat well the eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add to flour, mixing with spoon until soft dough forms.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: caramel crackers(snacks)
directions: Grease (or Pam) baking sheet.
Combine crackers and nuts on baking sheet.
In a saucepan, bring butter, sugar and syrup to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Pour syrup over crackers and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour a little bit of mixture onto wax paper and quickly break apart.
Continue until all of mix is separated.
If it hardens into a clump, return to oven until soft again.
Store in airtight container.
Yields approximately 9 cups.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook 1 to 2 pounds fettuccini; drain.
Melt butter in skillet. Mix White Sauce ingredients and cook until heated through.
Can add more milk.
Add fettuccini until heated through.

title: black bean dip
directions: Drain and rinse black beans. Combine all the ingredients in a microwave safe dish. Stir until blended. Heat in microwave until cheese is melted. Serve hot with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool, peel and then dice potatoes. Chop onion and garlic.
Add oil and vinegar to potatoes along with onion and garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all well. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: granola
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° until nicely toasted.
Makes 10 cups.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 1 inch apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until almost no imprint remains when touched with finger.
Immediately remove from baking sheet to wire rack; cool, then store in Tupperware.

title: chinese sugar rolls (biscuits)
directions: *You may want or need more or either of these.
Mix it to your taste.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Dice eggplant very small and soak overnight in salt water. Drain and rinse well.
Place eggplant in a saucepan; cover and simmer.
Soak bread crumbs in milk and set aside.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter for 15 minutes or until tender. Combine eggplant, bread crumb mixture and vegetable mixture; mix well.
Now add beaten eggs, pimento and seasonings.
Mix again and pour into a greased, long, oblong baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: salmon puff(may use tuna)
directions: Combine eggs, milk and soup.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into loaf pan or other small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until mixture appears set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick and easy quiche(makes 8 servings)
directions: Spray pie or quiche pan with nonstick vegetable coating spray. Sprinkle in onion, Canadian bacon, Swiss cheese and green pepper. Mix biscuit mix, egg substitute, milk, salt and pepper in a blender for 1 minute.
Pour mixture into a pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then cut.
Contains 143 calories and 5 grams fat per serving.

title: banana fritters
directions: Combine crumbs and sugar.
Cut bananas in half lengthwise and dip in orange juice.
Roll banana in crumb mixture.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet; dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine melted oleo, flour and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan on high fire for about 10 minutes or until sugar starts forming on inside of pan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Pour in buttered dish.

title: chocolate cherry upside-down cake
directions: Combine cornstarch, water and almond extract.
Stir to dissolve.
Blend in cherry pie filling.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir briskly until batter is smooth and blended. Pour evenly over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before inverting into serving dish.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Cut baking potatoes in half lengthwise.
Sprinkle cut sides with seasoned salt.
Top with a pat of margarine.
Turn, cut side down into baking pan and roast at 425° for 30 minutes or until done.
The longer they cook the browner and crispier the cut sides will become.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Combine vinegar, cocoa and food coloring together.
Add to mixture of sugar, butter and eggs.

title: frog egg salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Cool.
Bring water, remaining salt and oil to a boil.
Add pasta and cook until tender.
Drain; rinse and drain well. Combine egg mixture with pasta; mix lightly.
Chill overnight in fridge.
Next morning, add remaining ingredients.
Big Salad. Makes 25 servings.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, eggs and mandarin oranges.
Bake in 9x13in. pan at 350 degrees for 40 mins.

title: applesauce walnut cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs; mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 round pans.
Bake 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on pan at 350°.
Frost with cream cheese frosting when cool.

title: baked short ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in covered casserole in oven at 300° for 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
If you want thicker gravy, put flour, salt, pepper and paprika in bag with ribs before combining.
Serves 6 persons.

title: apricot stuffing
directions: In a small saucepan, over medium-high heat, combine celery, onion and turkey broth. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
In a large bowl, combine celery mixture, bread cubes, parsley, poultry seasoning, salt, egg whites and apricots.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake in oven the last 1/2 hour of turkey roasting time.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Set aside 1 cup cornbread stuffing mix and combine remainder with squash.
Add cream of chicken soup, undiluted, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture into casserole.
Sprinkle reserved stuffing mix on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cream-style corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour and butter in a pot and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes. Blend butter with flour and add to corn mixture. Mix well and remove from heat. Serves at least 6.

title: no knead oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little warm water. Add all the other ingredients to the 1 1/2 cups hot water. Add the yeast.
Stir in the eggs and raisins; mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight. Shape into loaves and let rise until doubled in size. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: brown and white kisses
directions: Separate eggs about 1 hour before making kisses.
Leave in bowl at room temperature.
Heat oven to 250°.
Beat egg whites. Slowly beat in sugar, a tablespoon at a time.
Beat until stiff, glossy and sugar is dissolved.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by round teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet, covered with heavy brown or white paper.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; remove with spatula.
Makes 40.

title: date coconut balls
directions: Cook egg, sugar and chopped dates in pan until dates are melted, stirring constantly.
Take from fire and add vanilla, chopped nuts and Rice Krispies.
Cool and form into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and sift together; set aside. Combine fruit and nuts, also set aside.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla in mixing bowl and whip on medium speed for approximately 3 minutes or until well blended and light.
Add fruit and nut mixture, stir to combine.
Add dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Portion into muffin tins, lined with paper.
(Fill nearly full so they overflow somewhat to look like a chef's hat.)

title: cherry-skillet cake
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch in 9-inch skillet, add cherries, juice, salt and extracts.
Cook over low flame, stirring constantly 3 minutes, or until juice is thick and clear.
Place cake layer on top of mixture, cover, continue cooking over very low flame for 5 minutes or until cake is heated through.
Invert on serving plate and serve with whipped cream.

title: sugar cookies (fluffy)
directions: Mix together the sugar and Crisco; add eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder to flour and then add soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add the flour mixture to the Crisco mixture alternating with buttermilk.

title: cheese custard(grandmother byrd's)
directions: Beat eggs separately. Cream sugar and butter. Add yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 pie crusts. Bake at 375° until brown and set.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until fluffy; add sugar gradually.
Stop beating.
Add (fold in) chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put in oven and immediately turn off oven (leave in about an hour).

title: chicken with eggplant
directions: Spray vegetable oil on skillet.
Dredge chicken breasts in crumbs and brown.
Set aside.
Salt eggplant slices which have been peeled and let stand 15 minutes.
Pat off with paper towel the excess water.
Dip eggplant into bread crumbs and layer on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes, until tender.

title: jill's berry crisp
