directions: *To toast oats, place in dry frying pan over medium heat. Heat until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° until sausage is done.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time to shortening and sugar mixture, beating well between each addition.
Add vanilla to milk, then add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed sugar mixture.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack to cool immediately after baking.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: saunders frosting
directions: Scald milk and cool slightly. Cream the butter and Crisco until light and fluffy. Add sugar to butter mixture. Add egg and vanilla. Add milk in small amounts while mixer is on medium to high speed until all mixed. Spread while at room temperature. Makes enough for 2 layers of cake.

title: "mom's" 1944 old english pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, then flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: no name hot dish
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: john's no chocolate, chocolate chip cookies
directions: Buy a bag of Nestle chocolate chips. Throw away the chips. Follow the directions on the bag except for the addition of the chips. Add toasted coconut, almonds and vanilla to recipe and you're done.
Enjoy choc-free goodness!

title: blackened seasoning powder
directions: Heat heavy medium skillet (preferably cast-iron) over medium-high heat.
Add all ingredients, except paprika, and stir until aromatic and beginning to darken, about 3 minutes.
Grind finely in spice grinder or in mortar with pestle.
Blend in paprika.
Use to flavor fish and poultry dishes.
Makes about 1/3 cup.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, the shortening and eggs thoroughly.
Blend in flour.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoon into balls; roll balls in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until serving. Garnish with fresh wedges of pineapple.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix butter, granulated sugar and 2 cups flour.
Press this in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Beat egg, brown sugar, remaining flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Add vanilla, nuts and apricots.
Spread over baked layer and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hot party crab canapes
directions: Combine Swiss cheese, mayo, mustard, salad dressing and lemon juice; mix well.
Fold crabmeat into cheese mixture.
Spread generously on bread squares.
Place on baking sheet with bread squares.
Preheat broiler and cook until lightly browned.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour and shortening, add well beaten egg, salt, vinegar and water.
Roll out. You can keep this dough up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Make small balls from sausage and fry.
Remove from skillet. Pour off grease, leaving about 1 tbsp.
Stir in chopped scallions. Stir and fry a few minutes, then add garlic.
When done, but not dark, remove from skillet.
In large bowl, mix cooked rice, soup and water chestnuts.
Mix well.
Add sausage, onion and garlic and stir.
(If mix seems dry, add 1 cup of chicken bouillon.)
Put in casserole dish and bake uncovered at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange nutbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in cranberries, nuts and orange peel.
Combine egg, orange juice and Crisco oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake in a greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes, or until done.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread 1 cut-up chicken with mayonnaise. Place on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown.

title: fudge cake
directions: To use butter or margarine instead of shortening, decrease milk to 2/3 cup.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain meat in pan; add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 hour. Rinse and drain all the beans and hominy before adding them to the meat.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet until completely brown.
Drain grease from meat.
Add Velveeta cheese until mixture is creamy. Spread on slices of rye bread.
Serve warm and enjoy.

title: poinsettia cookies
directions: Beat together powdered sugar and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and rum extract; mix.
Add flour, salt and shredded coconut; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten cookies with bottom of glass dipped in granulated sugar. Place a butterscotch morsel in center of each cookie.
Take candied cherries and cut in thin wedges.
Place wedges in strips down from butterscotch chips, alternating red and green until you have a circle to resemble a poinsettia.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Over hot (not boiling) water, combine Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels, corn syrup, shortening and water; stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat but keep mixture over hot water.
Dip pretzels into chocolate mixture to coat evenly.
Place pretzels on wire racks set over waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator until coating sets (about 10 minutes).
Remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature until surface dries, about 1 hour.
Makes 25 to 30 pretzels.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, syrup, and eggs; beat until smooth. Stir in mashed potatoes.
Spoon mixture into a greased baking dish.

title: charlie taylor's barbecue chicken
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except chicken, 15 minutes.
Use this to baste chicken halves as you cook them on the grill.

title: baked fish with lemon-pepper crust
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl, combine bread crumbs, parsley, pepper and salt.
Set aside.
Dip fish into melted butter and coat both sides with crumb mixture.
Place on a baking sheet and bake until cooked through, yet flaky to the fork, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle lemon juice and serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch buttered dish, place 2 cans pie sliced apples.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of sugar over apples.
Mix together flour, brown sugar, oleo and 1/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and serve.

title: clam onion dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Stir before serving.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour mixture into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55-60 minutes.

title: double orange cooler
directions: Mix juice, club soda and milk in a pitcher.
Pour into tall glasses and top with a scoop of orange sherbet.
If a sweeter taste is preferred, add 1 to 1 1/2 cups sugar.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix oats, flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add melted butter to oatmeal mixture until crumbly.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: missouri glazed donuts
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add butter, sugar and salt; mix well.
Add beaten eggs; dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cool milk.
Add all of this together, then add flour gradually.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, approximately 50 or 60 minutes. Turn dough out on well floured cloth covered board.
Roll around lightly to coat dough with flour.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick; cut out donuts.
Let rise again almost double in bulk.
Fry in deep, hot oil for 3 or 4 minutes.
Drop immediately into glaze.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain tuna; add cream cheese and mix until smooth.
Then add chopped green onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Form this mixture into a ball shape, then roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well; roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Put in pecans or walnuts (3/4 of bag).
Shake and coat well each quarter of biscuits in sugar and cinnamon; place around Bundt pan.
(Half way put in remaining nuts.)
Melt butter, sugar and milk in saucepan until smooth.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Take cake out of Bundt pan as soon as it is removed from oven (turn upside down on plate).

title: eggplant-shrimp-rice dressing
directions: Saute the shrimp, onion, bell pepper, garlic and cooking oil together. Add cooked eggplant to onion mixture. Cook until moisture is gone. Season with red and black pepper to taste. Combine rice with eggplant mixture.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Heat soups and oleo in saucepan.
Take out 1 cup and set aside.
Add rice to soup mixture and stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and lay chicken on top.
Pour remaining cup of sauce over chicken.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Watch while baking.
If chicken gets too brown, cover with tinfoil.

title: jellied pretzel salad
directions: Blend with pastry
blender.
Stir well and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: party iced tea
directions: Boil tea in water and let steep for 10 to 15 minutes.
Strain into 1 gallon jug.
Add sugar, lemonade and ginger ale.
Fill jug with water.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and bake, covered, in a slow oven at 300° for 3 hours.
Stir a couple of times during cooking.
During the last 20 minutes, add cheese and let it melt through casserole.
Serve with cornbread.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, egg, spinach, salt, oregano and pepper.
Grease a large 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and layer sauce, noodles and cheese mixture.
Top with the rest of the sauce and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Let stand before cutting.

title: hungarian potato soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add potatoes, salt and 1 cup water.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Blend flour, paprika, sour cream and milk until smooth.
Add to potato mixture.
Heat, stirring, for 1 minute.
Season to taste.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli chicken bake
directions: Boil chicken, celery, onions, and mushrooms.
Drain and set aside.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Combine sauce mixture with chicken and vegetables.
Remove broccoli from pkg. and squirt with the lemon.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add poppy seed, the cup of hot water and nuts.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bread a la neiman-marcus(this recipe is also a dessert.)
directions: Mix first
ingredients
and	spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend
and	pour
remaining
ingredients
over the first mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.	Time of preparation: 30 minutes.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: lemon peel; rose
directions: Peel the lemon, using a sharp vegetable peeler and cutting with a zigzag motion.
Cut in spiral, making a continuous strip about 1/2-inch wide.
Lay peel out on a work surface, yellow side down.
Roll one end of the peel tightly to make the center of the rose.
Loosely roll the remaining peel around, making it looser as it extends out.

title: mixed baked beans
directions: Cook bacon crisp; reserve drippings and crumble bacon.
Set aside.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Combine all else and spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: neapolitan pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with spices/herbs; brown in oil.
Add tomatoes; simmer for 30 minutes, or until chops are tender.
Stir in olives and serve over noodles.

title: hot punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook 3 hours in crock-pot on low.

title: chocolate ice cream sauce
directions: If real margarine is not available, use butter.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Press together with fingertips until dough forms a ball.
Pinch off pieces and roll into marble size balls.
Arrange 1-inch apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bottoms are golden brown. Makes about 3 dozen appetizers.

title: spiced pineapple sparkle
directions: Mix well and enjoy.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water, vanilla and raw peanuts.
Cook over low heat until peanuts begin to pop.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Stir well.
Spread real thin on greased pan.
Let set to cool.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together.
Spread on crust and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Spread lightly with frosting or powdered sugar while warm.

title: becky's vegetable soup(low calorie, low sodium)
directions: Heat oil and saute onion until soft. Add carrot, celery, garlic and seasonings.
Saute 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: 4 a's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease and flour baking pan(s).
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Yields 4 medium loaves, 2 large loaves or 8 mini loaves.

title: no bake mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix cheesecake crumbs with butter and sugar in bottom of muffin cups.
Beat milk and filling on low until blended.
Beat 3 minutes. Filling will be thick.
Spoon over crumbs in muffin cups. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, oatmeal, egg, chili powder, onions, salt, pepper and tomato juice or tomato sauce.
Put in 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Take out and drain juice.
Melt margarine.
Add flour to melted margarine in saucepan. Add milk to this mixture.
Bring to boil.
Add cheese and Mexicorn. When cheese is melted, pour over meat loaf and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and put in a 9 x 11-inch pan or medium casserole.
Mix the next two ingredients together and put over the carrot mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter roll-ups(kids love it!)
directions: You will need a knife, rolling pin and toothpicks.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Mix marinade ingredients well (shake in jar and blend with whisk).

Pour over chicken breasts and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Grill breasts over hot coals for approximately 20 minutes or until done. Turn once or twice during grilling time and baste with remaining marinade. Serve with brown rice and fresh green salad.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into pie shells.

title: slow-cooker cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover.
Cook on low 7 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place in a buttered 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugars, butter and cinnamon until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream, ice cream or milk.

title: fried pies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, cream and Crisco oil.
Blend together. Add flour and knead.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Form into walnut-size ball.
Roll as round as saucer.
Place fillings in center.
Fold in half and take fork, seal edges.
Drop in hot Crisco.
Fry until slightly brown.
Flip over and fry other side.

title: spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, pepper, celery, 2 tablespoons water and 1/2 tablespoon salt in skillet for 10 minutes.
Heat 1 1/2 cups water to almost boiling.
Add beef style seasoning or soy sauce and TVP. Add TVP mixture, tomato puree, tomato paste, oregano leaves, sweet basil, garlic powder and honey to sauteed vegetables.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, mix potatoes, sour cream, cheese, soup and onion.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and drizzle with melted butter. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Keeps well. Can be frozen.

title: lime jello
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; set in fridge to begin to congeal. Combine marshmallows, sugar, pineapple, cheese, salt and juice. Mix well. Fold in whipped cream. Mix this with the Jell-O. Can be made the night before and kept in the fridge.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Thaw lemonade.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients; pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Can use graham cracker pie shell.
Makes 2. Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain potatoes and mash. Mix with other ingredients. Put in greased dish and bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes. Cover with topping and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer. Knife inserted in center should come out clean when done.

title: shrimp cocktail cheese
directions: Mix sauce and shrimp.
Serve over block of cream cheese with assorted crackers.

title: fast and easy cheese pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in big skillet.
Place in oven.
Drain grease from pork chops.
Pour Tater Tots in a skillet and can of soup with milk.
Mix well.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Serves 6.

title: lavender lemonade
directions: Boil 2 1/2 cups of water with the sugar.
Add the lavender stems and remove from heat.
Place on the lid and let cool.
When cool, add the remaining water and the lemon juice.
Strain out the lavender.
Serve the Lavender Lemonade with crushed ice and garnish with lavender blossoms.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes (keep them stiff).
Season to taste with salt and pepper (Krazy salt works best).
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and hot water.
Add bread and let soak until mixture is lukewarm.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and place casserole in shallow pan.
Fill pan with hot water to 1-inch depth.
Bake in 350° oven until a sharp bladed knife inserted near center of pudding comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Press meat in a 9-inch round glass cake dish.
Spread catsup over top of meat loaf.
Microwave 15 to 17 minutes.
Give dish a 1/4 turn twice during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut up meat, bite size pieces.
Put in flour, garlic salt or powder and pepper.
Take meat out of flour and fry until brown. Put in covered glass casserole dish with 2 cans of French onion and cooking wine.
Cook 50 minutes at 350°.
Take out; add 2 cans cream of mushroom soup and 1 pint of sour cream mix.
Put back in oven for 10 minutes.
Take out.
Serve hot over noodles, rice or mashed potato.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix well and make into balls, then flatten.
Bake at 300° until they start to brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Top with mixture of soup and sour cream.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Pour melted butter over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Whiz in a blender.
Serve in elegant glasses with an orange slice as a garnish.

title: pumpkin harvest cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a small bowl, whisk together the flour, pumpkin pie spice and baking soda.
In medium bowl with an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in pumpkin puree. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Beat flour mixture until just combined. Stir in white chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoons 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes or until set.

title: filled cabbage
directions: Cut stem out of large cabbage and boil for 15 minutes.
Cool well.
Shave thick part of each leaf.

title: pineapple pies
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add flour and margarine.
Gradually add pineapple and milk.
Bake in 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 15 minutes to brown.
Makes 2 each 9-inch pies.
(Use unbaked pie crust for this recipe.)

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in a large mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese, onion, eggs and flour.
Beat on medium speed until blended.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice steak into 1/2-inch strips; brown in large pot and add 1/2 cup water, bell peppers and onions and add to mixture.
Let simmer on medium heat 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste and soy sauce; add 2 cups water and gravy mix.
Let cook 20 minutes.
Serve over hot rice!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar and last, fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour in crust.
Chill and serve.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef until no longer pink; drain.
Combine all ingredients except beans; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add beans.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile, melt margarine in saucepan over low heat and add caramels, stirring constantly.
Mix with condensed milk and pour over baked layer. Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter over caramel layer and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake for an additional 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix peppers, zucchini and onions.
Add salt.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Add vinegar and sugar. Simmer 45 minutes.
Put in jars and water bath.

title: baked brie
directions: Scrape rind from top of cheese.
Arrange almond slices over top, pressing firmly into cheese.
(Can be prepared 1 day in advance up to this point.)
Bring to room temperature.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding chocolate chips last.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
In large bowl, mix corn, eggs and onion well.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir into corn mixture. Add butter or margarine and pimientos.
Mix well.
Pour into dish.
Set dish in pan.
Pour hot water to 1-inch around dish. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until pudding is firm and knife comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese and beef casserole
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 cup cheese, bread crumbs, milk, onion and egg.
Make 24 (1 1/4-inch) meatballs.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. In rectangular baking dish, alternate 2 layers of potatoes, green beans and flour mixture.
Heat remaining cheese and mushroom soup until cheese melts.
Pour half of mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Arrange meatballs over potatoes.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Bake an added 45 minutes, until potatoes are tender.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Brush bread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon. Cut each slice into quarters. Arrange in layers in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle each layer with raisins.
Beat eggs and stir in remaining sugar, milk and vanilla. Continue stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over bread and raisins.
Set baking dish in pan containing 1-inch hot water. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes clean. Serve warm or cold.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.

title: mints
directions: Mix butter, egg white, extract and food coloring together. Add powdered sugar and knead until smooth.
Press into molds. Remove and let dry overnight.
Store in covered container.
(Roll pieces in powdered sugar before molding to keep from sticking.)

title: cheese and crackers hawaiian
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons syrup.
Blend pineapple with cheese and bacon.
Stir in syrup.
Pack cheese mixture into crock.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 5 cups.

title: mildred's cut out cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; mix in milk, egg and vanilla until blended.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt, then add to creamed mixture and stir until moistened.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Put in tightly covered bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll out 3/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface and cut with sharp metal cookie cutters and bake for 13 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Cookies will not brown.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar, medium speed.
Add eggs and blend well. Add baking powder to flour and then add milk and flour alternately to mixture; add vanilla; do not overbeat.

title: chilled melon soup
directions: Peel and remove seeds from melons.
Dice and put through food processor.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix to incorporate. Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, except yeast.
In separate bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
To this add chicken stock. Add to dry ingredients.
Knead mixture for 3 minutes.
Dough will be quite stiff (if too stiff, add extra liquid or an egg).

title: savory pie
directions: Mix grated cheese, bacon and peas.
Blend eggs and milk together.
Mix flour, mustard and parsley with milk.
Mix everything together.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350° in a 12 x 12-inch pan (sprayed with nonstick spray or greased with butter or margarine).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Put food color in a cup and add vinegar.
Mix well and add to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Mix cocoa, flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour mix and buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in 3 or 4 thin layer pans or an extra large cookie sheet at 350° until done.
Let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into ball.
Cover with waxed paper. Chill.

title: kielbasa hash
directions: Cut kielbasa into coins; dice potatoes and onions.
Place coins in frying pan on low heat until fat runs from meat.
Add potatoes and onions into pan.
When potatoes are cooked, serve. Must be stirred frequently or it will stick.
Very tasty.

title: hawaiian ham patties
directions: Mix together ham, canned milk, cracker crumbs, onions, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in a greased pan.

title: glowing salad
directions: Put each lettuce leaf on a plate.
Lay a pineapple slice on top of each lettuce leaf.
Stand 1/2 banana in the hold of each pineapple slice.
Top bananas with salad dressing.
Place a cherry on top of each banana to make your salad glow.

title: pecan pie cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients on low speed.
Pat down in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix the beaten eggs, 1 1/2 cups sugar and Karo syrup real well, then fold in pecans.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set, at 350°.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Blend at slow speed the cake mix, 1/2 cup of sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time; add sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Mix together 4 tablespoons of sugar and 3 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Use a small portion of sugar-cinnamon mixture instead of flour in greased pan.
Grease and "flour" a large Bundt pan or loaf pan. Pour half of cake mixture into pan.
Sprinkle half of sugar-cinnamon mixture on batter and add pecan pieces to taste. Add remaining batter.
Use remaining sugar-cinnamon-pecan mixture on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: no fat cookies
directions: Stir oil and sugar.
Add rest of wets.
Stir.
Add dries.
Add oats.
Stir.
If mixture seems too wet, try chilling it for awhile. Drop by spoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderately hot 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Combine all but last 3 ingredients, mix lightly.
Shape into loaf.
Combine ketchup, sugar and water.
Pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: basic pralines
directions: Cook all, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir until it begins to lose its gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
If it becomes too thick, reheat slowly.
Real easy.

title: potluck corn pudding
directions: Brush 3-quart shallow baking dish generously with some of the melted margarine.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together until well blended.
Pour mixture into prepared casserole and spread evenly on top.
Place pan on center shelf of oven and bake at 350° until top is golden and crusty and knife inserted into center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: clams al forno
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place clams in single layer baking dish.
Scatter all the remaining ingredients, except the scallions and lemon wedges, over the clams.
Roast the clams at 500° for 9 minutes.
Turn them and roast for 9 minutes longer, until they pop open.
Discard any that don't open.

title: wonderful baked beans
directions: Mix baked beans, catsup, brown sugar, onion and mustard. Sprinkle 1/2 can French fried onion rings into mixture and 1/2 on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat peanut butter and butter until melted.
Add powdered sugar until creamy and smooth.
Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut before cooling.
Cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown together in skillet hamburger and bacon.
Add onion when partially brown to cook until tender.
Drain grease.
Drain liquid from lima and kidney beans and reserve to add if needed.
Mix all ingredients together and place in crock-pot on low.
Heat for 2 to 3 hours, adding some of the reserved liquid if needed.
I vary the kinds of beans and also use regular mustard instead of dry sometimes.
If desired, you may increase the amount of hamburger or brown sugar.
It is a flexible recipe; you can use what you have on hand.

title: manicotti stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Take 1 shell.
Spoon a tablespoon of cheese mixture into middle of shell.
Fold both sides over to the middle.
Do the same with rest of shells.

title: mexican rice
directions: In a lightly oiled cooking skillet, stir-fry the rice, chopped onion and the seasonings over a medium flame until the rice is lightly golden brown.
Pour 2 of the cups of hot chicken broth and the small can of tomato sauce.
Very important:
After adding the chicken broth, do not stir the rice while it is cooking.
Let the rice come to a boil in the uncovered cooking skillet.
Cover the rice and let simmer over a low flame.
As the broth begins to evaporate from the skillet, gradually add the other 1 cup hot chicken broth to the rice.
Continue simmering over a low flame until all the chicken broth has evaporated.
Remove from heat and serve hot.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: shepherd's pie(easy)
directions: Thaw hash browns and meat ahead of time.
Combine meat, milk and dry soup mix.
Fill pie shell with this mixture.
Top with hash browns.
Add top crust.
Seal edges and pierce top in several places.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until brown.

title: sausage-breakfast casserole
directions: Cut
up
bread.
Remove
crust
and
spread
bread with butter.
Place in
a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Spoon over bread slices. Add shredded
cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and 1 teaspoon salt. Mix well
and
pour
over
cheese.
Cover
casserole and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for about 80 minutes. Important:
Cool in pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Serve with fruits.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease a 7 x 11 or 9 x 9 inch baking dish.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: ann murphy's famous chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together (including chocolate chips).
Mix wet ingredients together and pour into dry ingredients.
Mix together well and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Place all
ingredients	in
a quart jar and shake until thoroughly mixed.
Or
it
can
be mixed in a bowl for 10 minutes. Store it
in
a jar in the refrigerator and it will keep for over 4 weeks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put squash in buttered casserole.
Mix other ingredients and pour over mixture.
Cover.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: amiee's easy chicken
directions: Mix together soups, sour cream, wine and 2 cans of water. Arrange chicken breasts in a baking dish and pour mixture over them.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: lime jello dessert salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O into boiling water with 1/2 cup sugar added.
Beat in cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and Pet milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in oleo.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Heat lightly before serving.
Excellent with Doritos, tortillas or little Pepperidge Farm breads.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour drained Veg-All over the chicken.
In a saucepan, mix and bring to a boil the broth and soup.
Pour this over the chicken mixture. Melt butter.
Add milk, flour and pepper; mix thoroughly to form batter.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mixed greens with oranges and red onion salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine greens, oranges and onions; set aside.
In small bowl, with wire whisk, blend oil, vinegar, honey, salt and pepper.
Drizzle over salad.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in medium-size saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and salt.
Bring to boiling.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes (mixture may steam).
Remove from heat.
Carefully stir in milk. Return to heat.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 10x sugar.
Beat until smooth and spreadable.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1-inch thick slices.
Place all ingredients in electric skillet.
Cover and simmer at 250° for an hour or until done and syrup is decreased.
Turn frequently.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo; melt cheese with onion and oleo.
Add soup and milk.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mamie eisenhower's tomato pudding
directions: Add boiling water to puree with salt and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Place bread cubes in a 1-quart casserole and pour butter over bread cubes.
Add tomato mixture and bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon roll
directions: Combine salmon and cream cheese, mixing well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pecans and parsley.
Chill well. Shape into 12-inch long log and roll in pecans and parsley. Roll up in foil or plastic wrap.
Chill well.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: gooey bars
directions: Melt butter in oven in jelly roll pan.
Put dry cake mix in. Press down.
Layer chocolate chips, Cheerios, marshmallows, and pour Eagle Brand condensed milk over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and pepperoni.
Place half in casserole, then a layer of pepperoni and cheese.
Repeat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spaghetti sauce may be used instead of paste and tomato sauce.

title: curry chicken or turkey or lamb or shrimp
directions: Follow Knorr direction, then add other ingredients.
Serve over rice.

title: drunken chicken
directions: Mix together in saucepan. Heat and stir until smooth. Pour over chicken pieces which have been placed in a large baking pan. Bake 250-300 degrees for 2 1/2-3 hours. Chicken gets golden brown and makes it's own gravy.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 1/4 cup juice.
Combine pineapple, reserved juice, garlic, lemon, catsup, honey, Worcestershire sauce, rosemary and salt.
Arrange chicken in 3-quart shallow casserole dish.
Pour pineapple mixture over chicken.
Cover, refrigerate overnight or at least 1 hour.
Remove chicken from dish.
Pour marinade into saucepan.
Stir in cornstarch.
Cook until sauce boils and thickens.
Brush sauce over chicken.
Bake in 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pick chicken off bite size.
Layer chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Put Veg-All and a bit of chopped onion next. Mix chicken broth and cream soup; pour over vegetables.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice Then rinse well.
Drain and put into a bigger pan. Add milk to cover.
Add cinnamon, sugar and butter.
Cool until heated well.
In another pan, put eggs. Beat well and add milk. Mix with rice filling.
Grease dish and bake at 350° for 35 mins.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler.
Beat until well blended.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, beating constantly.
Beat until mixture forms peaks. When icing is thick, about 7 minutes, add vanilla and beat well.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage into a bowl, put mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Add vinegar and grated carrots.
Stir and blend well, add sugar to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soak garlic in vinegar for 1 hour.
Mix all cheeses.
Add vinegar.
Add 5 ounces dried beef.
Chill until firm.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining dried beef.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: candied apples
directions: You will also need popsicle sticks.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with rolls.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over rolls.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over top.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into balls.
Before serving, roll in more powdered sugar.
These freeze well.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice berries in baked pie shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together; add to the crushed berries.
Boil until thick.
Add lemon juice and cool completely.
Pour over sliced berries.

title: chicken and rice medley
directions: Begin preparation of the rice first, in a rice cooker or boil it stovetop until fluffy.

title: clams with linguine
directions: Bring clam juice and wine to boil in saucepot.
Add clams, cover and cook until shells open, 5 to 6 minutes.
Transfer clams to bowl with slotted spoon; cool.
Remove from shells and coarsely chop.
(Discard any unopened clams.)
Add onions, carrots, celery, garlic, thyme and pepper flakes to clam juice.
Simmer over medium heat until vegetables are tender, 25 minutes.
Stir in chopped clams, parsley, oil and salt.
Toss sauce with pasta in serving bowl.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Beat the butter, egg and powdered sugar for 2 minutes. Then add Cool Whip, pineapple and chopped peanuts. Stir in chopped apples.

title: cheese ball iii
directions: Have all
cheese
at room temperature.
Beat until well blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Shape
in
ball and roll in nuts.
Top with maraschino cherry.
Refrigerate.
Serve with snack crackers.
The kinds and amount of cheese can be varied.

title: marie's italian burger
directions: Brown hamburger, add all other ingredients and cook for 45 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: angel walnut cake
directions: Whip egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar and continue to whip until they hold a point but are not dry.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar slowly, then the extract.
Sift rest of sugar and flour together.
Fold in small amount at a time, mixing as little as possible.
Add walnuts.
Bake in ungreased tube pan for 1/2 hour at 275°, then 1/2 hour at 325°.
Invert pan and let hang until cold.
This is good without frosting.
I do sometimes use a caramel frosting.

title: black forest cheesecake
directions: Spread cookie crumbs on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan coated with cooking spray.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese produce at high speed with mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Gradually add egg substitute, mixing well.
Add melted chocolate, cocoa and vanilla, mixing until blended.
Stir in sour cream alternative.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; run a knife
around edge of pan to release sides.
Let cool on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove sides of pan and spread with cherry pie filling. Dollop each serving with 1 tablespoon whipped topping.
Yields 12 servings.

title: seafood casserole
directions: In saucepan saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and cream.
Stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt, pepper, pimento, water chestnuts, parsley, crab meat, shrimp, rice and 1/2 cup (2 ounces) Cheddar cheese.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with rest of cheese around edge of dish, leaving center clear.

title: fajitas
directions: Use round steak or sirloin. Trim fat from meat and puncture. Marinate 12 to 24 hours in 1/2 can of beer.
Grill meat, cut into strips. Serve with tortillas, lettuce, picante sauce, chopped tomatoes, guacamole, cheese, anything that you please.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook vermicelli and drain.
Stir in lemon juice and oil. Refrigerate.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except mayonnaise. Add to cold pasta mixture and toss with mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: In large saucepan, combine sweet potatoes with enough water to cover.
Boil until fork tender (not mushy), about 15 minutes. Drain potatoes but save the cooking liquid. In medium bowl, combine sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Stir to mix.

title: baked egg omelet
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet (with 1-inch sides) with foil.
Lay graham crackers to cover sheet.
Melt butter, sugar and pecans. Boil 1 minute. Spread over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 325° or 350°. Let cool in pan. Break apart and enjoy!

title: chocolate malt ice cream
directions: Mix and pour into a 6-quart freezer.
Add milk to fill line. Freeze.

title: hot mexican chicken salads
directions: Combine chicken, 1 cup cheese and next 8 ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill.
Heat 1/2-inch of oil in a large deep skillet until hot (375°).
Fry tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil until crisp and golden.
Drain on paper towels.

title: baked tomatoes and corn
directions: Slice off tops of tomatoes and scoop out insides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, basil.
Combine corn and green pepper and place in boiling salted water for 3 minutes.
Drain, add bacon, butter and pepper.
Stuff tomatoes, bake until soft at 350°.

title: rocky road
directions: Combine marshmallows and nuts and sprinkle evenly over the bottom of a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate in the top of a double boiler over hot water, stirring frequently.
Pour the melted chocolate evenly over marshmallow nut mixture.
Cool until firmly set and cut in 1-inch squares.

title: frosted seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add 7-Up.
Let partially congeal and then add crushed pineapple which has been drained of juice.
Add marshmallows and bananas.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until solid.

title: pasta sweet pudding(aletria)
directions: Place water, milk, butter, sugar, lemon juice, rind, pulp and salt together in a 4-quart or larger saucepan.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add cappelini or vermicelli; cook slowly over a low flame, using a long tined fork to separate the cappelini so that it will not stick together while cooking.
Cook vermicelli until tender, but do not overcook.
When cappelini or vermicelli is cooked, make sure that the sauce is thick but not dry.
Remove from flame and let it cool.

title: ham and asparagus mornay
directions: Arrange 4 spears of asparagus on each ham slice; roll and put in single layer in shallow pan.
Melt butter; mix in flour and stir until smooth.
Pour in cream and continue stirring until sauce is thick and bubbly.
Add cheese.
Add some of mixture to egg yolk, then return to pan.
Pour over ham rolls and bake for 35 to 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: oatmeal date squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Work in shortening. Pack 1/2 in loaf cake pan. Cover with date filling, then add rest of crumbs on top and bake 40 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In
a large bowl, cream oleo and sugar until fluffy. Add water and vanilla. Gradually add flour, then nuts, beating until firm.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart and bake until lightly brown on bottom.
Let cool on rack and roll in confectioners sugar. When completely cool, roll in sugar again.

title: chip dip potatoes
directions: Mix, place in
greased	casserole
and dot with butter. Bake covered at 350°
for 1 hour.
(May make ahead and refrigerate before baking.)

title: pate chinois
directions: Cook
hamburg with onion; salt and pepper.
Put a layer of mashed
potatoes
in
a
loaf
pan.
Place one half of the hamburg on
top of potatoes.
Put the corn on top of meat and add
the rest of the meat.
Put the peas on top of second meat layer.
Put a layer of mashed potatoes on top of peas; sprinkle the grated cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy jello dessert
directions: Make jello as directed on package.
Mix cottage cheese and jello together, then add pineapple.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator until firm, then serve.

title: layered enchilada pie
directions: Combine cooked meat, tomato sauce, water, onions and seasonings.
Simmer to blend on medium heat.
In casserole dish (sprayed with Pam), alternate layers of meat, tortillas and cheese until all ingredients are used.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: a favorite lettuce salad
directions: Toss lightly in large bowl or individual bowls.

title: monie's bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk until soft.
Add rest of ingredients and mash
together.
Pour in greased pans.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: nutty golden glow salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and stir until dissolved.
Add juices and salt.
Allow to thicken slightly.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts and turn into 5-cup mold or individual molds. Refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hungarian pork chops
directions: Brown chops and drain.
Add onion, spices and water.
Cover and simmer over low heat 1 hour. Transfer chops to warm platter. Add sour cream to gravy and blend.
Spoon over chops.
Serves 2.

title: barbecued black-eyes
directions: Brown meat. Saute onion and add to peas.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 200° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Great for barbecue or as side dish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise; remove stems and seeds.
Cook peppers 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain well.
Combine meat and next 3 ingredients in a nonstick skillet.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain and return to skillet.
Stir in corn and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into pepper halves.
Place peppers in a shallow baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: *Or substitute 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano for 1/2 teaspoon of the dried basil.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in pumpkin and water.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Spoon into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until bread tests done.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: sweet and sour mustard sauce
directions: Soak mustard overnight in vinegar. Beat egg yolks and sugar and add to mustard mixture.
Cook in microwave until thickened. Chill. Makes 2 cups.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients well.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 11 casserole and let set in refrigerator.

title: sweet red cucumber rings
directions: Mix water and lime.
(Contact may cause irritation or burns to skin and eyes.
Read opposite panel for first aid.)
Do not use aluminum container.
Soak cucumber rings in lime mixture for 24 hours.

title: barbecue ham in a can
directions: With a beer can opener, put about 6 to 8 holes on top of the can.
(Top is side where the key is.)
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: deep dish pie
directions: Melt butter in a deep dish.
Make a batter from flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour into melted butter.
Pour warm sweetened fruit into batter and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange pineapple slices and cherries on the sugar mixture.
Mix cake as directed on the package with 1 1/3 cups water and 2 eggs.
Beat as directed.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes for topping to begin to set.
Turn upside down onto large platter or cookie sheet.
Best if served warm with Cool Whip.

title: potato salad
directions: Potatoes need to have a mashed potato texture.
Mix ingredients.
Use a little vinegar for those who prefer the sweet to sour flavor.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries.
Let dry on paper towels overnight.
In a small bowl, combine butter, liqueur and corn syrup.
Stir in confectioners sugar; knead until smooth.
Cover.
Form a heaping 1/2 teaspoonful around each cherry.
Place on waxed paper covered cookie sheet; refrigerate.

title: hearty cheese fondue
directions: Combine buttermilk and flour in a saucepan.
Heat to a simmer but do not boil.
Gradually add cheese, stirring well, until cheese is melted.
Add seasonings and place in fondue pot over low flame. Dip using bread cubes, cherry tomatoes, raw cauliflowerets, or other vegetables.

title: trish's meal in a pouch
directions: Pat out turkey meat into large steak like patties.
Place on long strip of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle meat with salt, pepper and Lawry's seasoning.
Place potatoes, carrots and onion around and on top of meat.
Sprinkle Worcestershire and soy sauces liberally over all.
Fold aluminum foil up from long ends and fold over. Then fold up short sides and crimp together to seal.
Place "pouches" on long cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Yield: 2 pouches.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples and place in ungreased baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted margarine, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve with your favorite whipped topping.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey or pancake syrup.
Add powdered milk and coconut or cereal.
Roll into balls.
Use a teaspoon to measure size and refrigerate.

title: minty hot chocolate
directions: Heat milk and meltaways on High (microwave) 1 to 2 minutes. Mix.
Add Peppermint Schnapps.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix and let stand until firm. For a topping beat 1 egg, mix 1/2 c. sugar and 1/2 c. pineapple juice and 2 Tbls. flour. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool and add 3 ounces cream cheese, cream well. Fold in 1 package of dream whip.

title: prosciutto wrapped hearts of palm
directions: In a non-aluminum bowl, combine the vinegar, oil, thyme and pepper.
Cut the hearts of palm in half crosswise.
Wrap each piece in a slice of Prosciutto; secure with a toothpick.
Place the hearts of palm in the marinade; chill for 3 hours.
Remove palms from the marinade.
Place the arugula leaves on a serving platter. Arrange the wrapped hearts of palm on top.
Sprinkle with a grinding of pepper.
Serve at room temperature.

title: cheryl's chicken and rice soup
directions: Cook rice and onion according to package directions for rice in a large stockpot.
When rice is cooked add the remaining ingredients.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.
May need to add more chicken broth or milk to soup as the rice will soak up the liquid as it is cooked.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Blend all remaining ingredients except pineapple and peppers.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered.
Uncover and add pineapple and pepper strips.
Bake another 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine margarine, flour and pecans in bowl. Mix well. Press over bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix margarine and cookie crumbs (all but 1 1/4 cups crumbs) together and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread softened ice cream on top of cookie crumb mixture.
Put in freezer until ice cream is frozen again.
Spread fudge sauce and nuts on top of ice cream.
Then spread La Creme on top of that.
Sprinkle on leftover cookie crumbs.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Let stand out a few minutes before cutting.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a hole in center.
Pour in all liquid ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornish hens and stuffing
directions: Season hens inside and out with salt and pepper.
Cook rice according to instructions on box.
Melt butter/margarine in pan and add onion, celery, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until onion and celery are soft and brown.
Mix well with rice and stuff the hens.
Place breast on rack in shallow roasting pan and brush well with butter.
Roast uncovered in 400° oven about 1 hour or until tender.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water 5 to 7 minutes or until tender. Drain. Place cabbage in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper, mixing well. Pour over cabbage. Combine bread crumbs and butter, stirring well. Sprinkle over cabbage. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add sherbet and mix well until sherbet dissolves. Place in fridge until partially set (about 10 minutes). Fold in oranges and whipped cream. Chill.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add crushed pineapple and 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Let jell.
Put mini marshmallows on top of jello after jelled.
In saucepan, combine eggs with 2 cups reserved pineapple juice (add water to make 2 cups, if necessary).
Add sugar and flour and cook until thick.
Let cool and pour over marshmallows. Mix cream cheese, Dream Whip and milk until fluffy and put over top.
Toasted coconut can be used as a garnish on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, 1 stick margarine, white sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Put into casserole dish. Mix cornflakes, 1 stick margarine, brown sugar and nuts. Sprinkle on top of sweet potato casserole.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Yields 2 pies.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into two pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 300° and bake until firm.

title: martha's cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll into balls and then roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in cellophane and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: incredible cookie
directions: Cut the cookie dough into 1/2-inch slices; arrange on an ungreased 14-inch round pizza pan, then press the slices together. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until the cookie is done. Let cool.
Spread the pudding over the cookie.
Arrange the banana slices on the pudding.
Slice in pie-shaped wedges.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Frost cooled cake or cupcakes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet or roll in a roll, wrap in wax paper and store in refrigerator.
Slice and bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Put in large airtight container.
Label.
Store in cool, dry place.
Use within 6 months.
Makes about 17 cups of hot chocolate mix.
Put 3 to 4 tablespoons mix in cup of hot water per serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. May need extra milk to get correct thickness. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and deep-fry.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook over low heat until thick.
Let cool.
Pour over strawberries that have been arranged in a prebaked pie crust. Chill until set.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix together; pour on hot griddle.
Enjoy with your favorite topping.

title: skillet squash au gratin
directions: Mix first four ingredients gently with salt.
Heat the margarine in a large skillet until hot.
Pour the vegetables into skillet.
Cover tightly.
Cook at medium heat for about 8 minutes, stirring gently twice.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mixture.
Cover and cook until cheese is melted.

title: ham and cabbage soup
directions: Cook onion and celery in melted butter in heavy cook pot until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in water and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is boiling.
Add cabbage and bay leaf.
Cover.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Stir in ham and cook 3 to 4 minutes. Gently blend in sour cream.
Heat
a few minutes.
Do not boil. Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients in order given in a large mixing bowl. Form into 1-inch balls and place on a baking sheet (ungreased). Bake for 15 minutes. May be frozen, uncooked.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix water, rice and margarine together; let stand 5 minutes. Add soup; mix well.
Cook and drain broccoli by directions on package.
Stir broccoli into rice mixture.
Add cheese.
Pour into bake dish.
Cover with lid or foil; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "our" carrot cake
directions: Thoroughly stir together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon. In a large bowl, beat eggs until frothy. Slowly beat in oil. Gradually add the flour mixture, beating until smooth. Mix in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until done (about 40 minutes). Cool on rack and frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate-swirl coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Stir coconut, nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon melted butter together; set aside.
Mix baking mix, remaining sugar and butter, egg and milk together.
Beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Pour into pan.
Spoon chocolate over batter with knife.
Cut through batter for marbled effect.
Sprinkle coconut mixture evenly on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Check 10 to 12 minutes as ovens vary.
These are a soft cookie and are very good!

title: (play dough) modeling dough
directions: Mix ingredients in a pan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from side of pan and becomes doughy in consistency. Knead until cooled.
Model different colors of clay.

title: scratch cake
directions: With an electric mixer, cream together margarine and sugar. Add eggs. Alternate flour and milk, ending with flour. If too thick, add more milk. Add vanilla. Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13 glass dish. Bake at 350° until top is slightly brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Top with your favorite homemade icing.

title: apple cake squares
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Cream margarine with sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture until combined.
Gently fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for about 40 minutes until done (toothpick test).
Let stand 15 minutes after baking.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: lavell's fudge
directions: Mix sugars and milk; cook for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and crackers.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Dissolve yeast in the warm water. Combine with warm buttermilk and melted shortening. Sift together salt, sugar, soda and flour. Add gradually to liquid mixture, beating smooth each time. Let stand in warm place 10 minutes, covered. Shape into rolls; let stand in a warm place for 30 minutes to rise. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 12 rolls.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Separate dough into eight triangles.
Place sausage on wide end and roll up.
Place tip down on an ungreased cookie sheet or baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Pull meat off bones and save broth.
Melt margarine and pour crumbs into it; mix well.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Add mayonnaise, grapes, oranges and almonds to chicken mixture; toss well.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Garnish with additional orange slices and grapes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat ingredients just enough to mix well and store in a container.
Keeps for a long time in the refrigerator.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until warm; do not boil.
Spoon a small amount of sauce in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Fill flour tortillas with chicken, sauce and cheese.
Roll up to enclose filling.
Arrange in dish.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: nutty pineapple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat two 4 1/4 x 8 3/4-inch loaf pans or six 5 3/4 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pans with cooking spray. Cream sugar and butter until smooth. Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy. Add pumpkin puree and milk. Combine flour, pecans, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture. Stir just until flour is moistened. Divide batter between prepared pans, smoothing tops. Bake large loaves for 55 to 60 minutes or smaller loaves for 45 minutes. Cool 5 minutes in pans. Turn onto wire rack. Cool completely.

title: baked squash
directions: Place in baking dish and cook 20 minutes in oven at 375°. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandma shock's butterscotch pie
directions: Mix slightly beaten egg yolks, milk, sugar and salt in a bowl and set aside. Melt butter in a large skillet. Stir in flour. Do not brown but cook. Add milk/egg mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Custard is done when a knife cuts through and leave a trough.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in greased and floured tube pan.
Mix 4 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over batter.
Add remaining batter to pan and sprinkle remaining sugar mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon yogurt coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-cup Bundt pan. In a large bowl, beat oil and honey until creamy.
Add egg, egg substitute and lemon extract.
Beat until blended.
In a medium bowl, combine flours and baking powder.
Stir into honey mixture alternately with yogurt.
Fold in lemon peel and cranberries. Pour into prepared Bundt pan; smooth top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cook in pan on wire rack.
To serve, invert coffeecake onto plate.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: strawberry banana pie
directions: Combine cheesecake mix and milk.
Beat until thick (about 2 minutes).
Fold drained strawberries and sliced bananas into mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: easy pecan turtles
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Place 3 pecan halves in shape of "Y."
Place caramel in middle.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes just until caramel melts.
Over low heat melt morsels and shortening.
Spoon over melted caramel.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Remove from foil and enjoy!

title: wassail bowl
directions: Stud oranges with cloves; place 1/2-inch apart in baking pan with a little water.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 30 minutes. Heat cider with 1 cinnamon stick to boiling.
Add brandy or rum. Pour into punch bowl; float baked oranges on top.
Serve in cups or mugs, using cinnamon sticks for stirring.

title: warm bean and spinach salad
directions: Remove large stems from spinach; tear spinach into bite size pieces. Place in a large bowl. Add beans; set aside. Heat bell pepper and dressing to boiling in 1 qt. saucepan; reduce heat to low. Cook uncovered 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in garlic pepper. Pour bell pepper mixture over spinach and beans; toss. Sprinkle with cheese. Serve warm.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix softened ice cream and Cool Whip together. Add crushed cookies to this mixture.
Pour into the two cookie crusts. Cover with foil and freeze.
After frozen, let sit a few minutes and then cut and serve.

title: penuche
directions: Stir sugar, salt and water over low heat until sugar dissolves. Boil slowly without stirring to the soft ball stage, 238° (when a spoonful of mixture is dropped in a cold small bowl of water, it will form a soft ball capable of being picked up).
Add butter; do not stir.
Place saucepan in bowl of cold water.
When bottom of pan is cool, beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Do not overbeat.
Drop candy from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: mexican hot dog casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain Ro-Tel.
Dice onion and bell pepper.
Add red pepper, black pepper, garlic powder and any other favorite spices to taste.
Mix in chili and simmer on medium heat. While sauce simmers, split hot dogs lengthwise 3/4 of the way through.
Slice off 4 slices of cheese 1/2 inch thick and cut them into 4 strips.
Place 2 strips in each hot dog.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Add cranberry sauce, celery and nuts.
Put half of jello mixture in a dish or mold.
Let harden.
Spread with sour cream.
Add the remainder of jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Let harden.

title: frozen brownie sundae
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix brownie mix with water, oil and egg.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.
Spread softened ice cream evenly over cooled brownies; press peanuts into ice cream.
Place in freezer until firm.

title: fruit with almond cream
directions: Combine all ingredients, except toasted almonds and fruit. Place fruit in small serving bowls; cover with almond cream. Chill for 1 hour.
Garnish with toasted almonds before serving.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt together margarine and cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, pecans and vanilla; mix well.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Place chicken in bottom of a casserole.
Place a bacon strip on top of each chicken breast.
Mix the soup and sour cream. Place over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn; reserve liquid.
Measure 1 cup of corn.
Add enough milk to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Combine egg, milk mixture and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until moistened.
Drop batter from tablespoon into deep, hot fat (375°).
Fry until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with warm syrup or powdered sugar.

title: zucchini me yaurti
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in olive oil over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 more minutes or until tender. Combine last 5 ingredients; pour over squash.
Heat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned bread
directions: Mix and knead together; roll out and pat.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sauerkraut balls(this is an unusual recipe, but good.)
directions: In a bowl, mix sauerkraut, ham and pepper.
Make into small ball shapes and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in skillet of hot grease or Fry Daddy until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup pecans.
Form in a ball.
Chill and roll in pecans.

title: brunch for a bunch
directions: Cook sausage; drain and crumble.
Lightly grease pan.
Place potatoes in dish and sprinkle with salt.
Layer with crumbled sausage, cheese and bell pepper.
Mix eggs and milk together thoroughly.
Pour over bell peppers.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: In heavy pan, brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: white trash
directions: Mix cereals, pecans and pretzels together. Melt white chocolate and pour over cereal mixture. Stir until coated. Spread on wax paper. Let cool and then break into pieces.

title: frozen coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the salt to the flour.
Reserve 2 tablespoons flour to mix with the coconut.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Add flavorings and beat.
Mix the reserved flour with the coconut; stir into the batter.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Start cake in cold oven.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well in mixer.
Grease Bundt pan, then sprinkle with sugar.
Pour into pan and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sandra's fresh fruit salad
directions: Peel oranges down to the pulp or just below skin.
With sharp knife, remove orange sections.
Scrape excess pulp or squeeze to get all of juice.
Cut apples int small bite-size pieces.
Add pineapple, including juice.
Add Fruit Fresh.
Add sliced bananas and cherries, cut in half.
Do not add cherry juice unless you prefer it.

title: easy does it donuts
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, egg and melted shortening.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to liquid mixture.
Stir lightly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into heated shortening.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: mushroom and brown rice skillet
directions: In large skillet, saute celery, onion and garlic in margarine for about 5 minutes, or until celery is crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve bouillon.
Cover and steam over low heat without stirring for 50 minutes, or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Let stand covered 10 minutes before serving.
Fluff rice lightly with fork. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook potatoes and onion in enough water to cover on medium heat until tender.
Drain water.
Add cubes of cream cheese.
Remove from heat and stir until cream cheese is melted.
Add soups, butter, milk, and spices.
Serve hot.
May be topped with shredded cheese, bacon bits, or green onion tops.

title: souper enchiladas
directions: In an 8-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, fry tortillas one at a time, 2 to 3 seconds per side.
Drain on paper towels.
Cook onion and garlic in leftover oil in skillet until tender.
Stir in soup, meat, water, cumin and chilies.
Heat through.
Spoon about 1/3 cup soup mixture onto each tortilla. Roll up; place seam side down in oblong dish and pour picante sauce over tops and sprinkle cheese over that.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In a large
saucepan, heat the olive oil and margarine; saute the onions until
limp.
Add
the
peas
and carrots and cook for just a
minute, stirring.
Then add the rice and stir to coat
the rice
with
the margarine and oil.
Then add the chicken broth and
a
little salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until rice is just tender and each grain is separate.
Taste for seasoning.
Serves 4.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef; add tomato paste, tomato sauce, mushrooms, onions, garlic, basil, parsley, salt, oregano, pepper and water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Prepare filling by combining cottage cheese, egg, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Alternate layers of lasagne noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and cheese in a 13 x 9-inch pan (3 layers high).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: glazed fruit compote
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice (you will need 1 1/2 cups of juice).
Drain the water from the oranges and discard.
Mix pineapple juice, lemon juice and pudding mix and cook until shiny and thick.
Cool.
Drain off accumulated juice from fruits.
Add strawberries and sliced bananas just before serving.
Glaze the fruit with the cooled pudding mixture and place in a glass bowl; toss lightly.

title: layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch Tupperware in order given.
Spread top with mayonnaise and cheese.
Sprinkle with Bac*Os.
Seal tightly with foil or lid.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep a week in Tupperware.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend with sugar mixture.
Add chopped apples.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake 1 hour, until done, in a 350° oven.
The cake mixture will be very thick and will result in a very moist, delicious cake.
If desired, garnish with whipped cream.

title: fruit glazed custard with coconut
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs, coconut extract, condensed milk, and coconut until smooth.
Pour into partially baked pie crust and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Combine currant jelly, flavored liqueur, cornstarch and water in medium saucepan and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature. Arrange sliced fruit and blueberries in a circular pattern on top of custard.
Brush on glaze.
Chill and serve.

title: cranberry-orange-apple relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and refrigerate until time to serve.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: irish potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mash with butter and small amount of milk.
You can either saute onion or cook in with potatoes. Add just enough sage to lightly season.
Pour into uncooked pie crust and top with another crust.
Brush with milk. Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for approximately 45 minutes
to 1 hour.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add milk and sugar. Sift half the flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to egg and sugar mixture. Beat with beater or food processor until smooth. Add only as much remaining flour to make a batter thin enough to run through funnel.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix the ingredients except the margarine together.
Now put 1 stick of margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan and melt.
Now mix all the rest and pour a can of pie filling or fresh fruit on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° until crust comes to top and browns.

title: supreme delight dessert
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add cream cheese; mix well.
Mix in picante sauce.
Stir in mushrooms. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown, stirring every ten minutes.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 3 well-greased 1 pound coffee cans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serve with Philly cream cheese or plain.

title: crock-pot steak and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Roll in flour.
Brown in oil and drain. Layer in crock-pot.
In blender, blend mushroom soup and French onion soup and water, blend on high.
Pour over steak.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours, or overnight.

title: john's pineapple surprise jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water.
Use reserved pineapple juice and combine with water or clear soda to make 3/4 cup liquid. Stir into dissolved Jell-O.
Add sour cream and blend with whisk until smooth.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add drained, crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight until completely set.

title: texas "caviar"
directions: Put about 2 cups of beans, then oil and lemon juice into a food processor or blender and process until smooth.
Scrape into a large bowl.
Stir in remaining beans, the jalapeno pepper, scallions, garlic, salt and cumin.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours for flavors to blend.
Garnish with scallions and tomatoes just before serving.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, leaving egg whites until last. Put in 8 1/2-inch buttered pie tin.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Before serving, top with whipped cream.

title: stuffed grapevine leaves(warak dawali)
