directions: *Grapevine leaves, preserved in jars, may be found in specialty foodstores.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
In large bowl, put layer of wafers, layer of strawberries and layer of pudding mixture; repeat.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
In baking dish, in this order, put rice, broccoli and chicken.
Spread sauce over it.
Sprinkle cheese and Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix, mixed with butter, over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain corn, beans and peas.
Add pimento, green peppers, celery and onion.
Heat and bring to boil sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar, oil and water.
Allow to cool, then pour the mixture over the vegetables and refrigerate.
Will keep several days.

title: crabbies(makes 48 appetizers)
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients. Spread on muffins.
Freeze on cookie sheet until hard. Store in plastic bag in freezer until ready to use. Cut in quarters and heat under broiler.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature. Mix cream cheese and dressing together. Shape into a ball. Shake on topping. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a 10-inch pie pan or 13 x 9-inch baking dish at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa into a bowl.
Cream oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add food coloring.
Mix until blended.
Combine buttermilk and baking soda. Mix well; add oil-sugar mixture alternately with dry ingredients. Add vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon into 2 greased 9-inch round pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Combine milk and remaining sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Spoon evenly on each layer before frosting.
Cool.
Frosting recipe follows.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Spray Pam or grease lightly the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer uncooked rice in bottom of pan.
Brown pork chops and arrange on top of rice.
Pour both cans of soup and 1/2 can of water over all. Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 325° for approximately 2 hours.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put vegetables through food chopper.
Add remaining ingredients (spices should be tied in a cheesecloth).
Boil togetter for 2 hours or until thick.
Seal while hot in sterile jars.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Dab 1/2 teaspoon jam or jelly on top and return to oven 5 minutes.
These freeze or will keep in fridge.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Grease	a
1 1/2 quart round casserole and place 1/4 of the hominy in it.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of chili peppers and dot with 1/4
of
sour
cream.
Season lightly with salt.
Repeat these layers 3 more times.
Pour the cream over the casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookie dough mix as per directions on package on pizza tin.
Let cool when done.
Spread cream cheese on cookie to desired thickness.
Slice strawberries and kiwi fruit to desired thickness and place on top of cream cheese.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm, not hot, water.
Melt butter; add sugar in a large bowl.
Add beaten egg and dissolved yeast mixture.
Add flour and stir until thoroughly mixed.
To cook, drop by spoonfuls into well-greased 2 1/2-inch muffin tins and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until browned.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove pie crusts from freezer.
Invert 1 crust unto wax paper and allow to thaw until flat.
Trim the crimped edge off after crust is flattened for top.
Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon, grated rind of lemon and lemon juice.
Arrange slices of apples on side of chilled shell.
Dot with butter; cover with flattened crust.
Seal edges and crimp.
Cut several slits in top crust.
Bake on baking sheet, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan with cover, saute bacon.
Add onion, potatoes and 1 cup of water.
Simmer 10 minutes until tender, but not mushy.
Remove cover and set aside.
In saucepan with cover, simmer 10 minutes the corn, cream, sugar and butter.
Add to potato mixture and add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until heated.
Do not boil.

title: spicy hermit cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream the shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and rolled oats.

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a buttered 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Arrange bread fingers over peaches to cover top.
Combine sugar, flour, margarine and egg.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until golden.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli, cheese and bacon; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: blueberry delite
directions: Melt butter; add to cracker crumbs.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and mix. Press to bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese.
Beat until fluffy; add remaining sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread blueberry filling over the 2 layers.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: apple pudding
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Put on butter, then add milk.
Put apples in center on top of batter.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter Crisco; add milk and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add eggs last, one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peggi's city chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate over night.
Skewer meat to make 28 sticks.

title: old-fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat until soft, butter.
Add gradually and blend until light and creamy, sugar.
Beat in egg and marshmallows; have buttermilk ready.

title: krazy steak
directions: Brown onions and mushrooms in butter or margarine until onions are soft or brown.
Place 1/2 of mushrooms and onions in bottom of casserole dish.
Cut steak into thin strips.
Season steak while browning in butter or margarine with Krazy salt, steak seasoning, Worcestershire sauce and a little water to keep from sticking or burning.
Place over mushrooms and onions in casserole dish. Spoon over celery soup.
Use 2 cans if you want lots of gravy. Put remaining mushrooms and onions over steak and to with grated Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at about 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and salt, then pecans.
Shape into balls and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine in large bowl the oats, whole wheat flour, brown sugar, salt and margarine.
Pour over this the 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir in.
When batter has cooled to lukewarm, add the dissolved yeast.
Stir in the white flour, one cup at a time, until the dough is stiff enough to handle.

title: make and eat play dough
directions: Spoon out some big globs of peanut butter into a bowl.
Then pour a few spoonfuls of honey in.
Now add some powdered milk. Start mixing it all up with your hands.
Keep adding the powdered milk until it makes a good dough.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, onions and garlic; spread on bread halves.
If desired, sprinkle with parsley.
Wrap each half in foil.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Unwrap and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until puffed, but not brown.
Cut into slices.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: raspberry dream cake
directions: Slice cake into three layers.
Prepare Dream Whip.
Mash raspberries through a strainer so as to remove seeds.
Add a little raspberry juice to Dream Whip.
Add enough to make it light pink.
Spread whipped topping on cake layers.
Pour raspberries on top. (Sugar can be added to raspberries if not sweet enough.)

title: quick and easy pork chops
directions: Drain pork chops.
Add water and soup.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: red beet jelly
directions: In deep pan, put lemon juice, beet juice, pectin and jello. Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and boil 2 minutes.
Put in jelly glasses.

title: orange icebox cookies
directions: Crush vanilla wafers until very fine.
Melt oleo; add powdered sugar and juice.
Add crushed vanilla wafers and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Form into walnut-size balls and roll in coconut.
Store in a tight container and keep in refrigerator.
This recipe freezes well.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients, except soda, and add soda to buttermilk.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately.
Fold in prunes, nuts and vanilla.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms well and separate the stems from the caps. Chop the stems finely and saute them in oil for about 5 minutes or until they are soft.
Add the sherry and continue cooking a few minutes.
Mix in the seasonings and bread crumbs and stuff the mushroom caps.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bleu cheese ball
directions: Combine Bleu cheese, Old English cheese, cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt in bowl; mix well.
Shape into ball; roll in pecans.
Yield: 32 servings.

title: date salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and whipped cream.
Add nuts, dates, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix and put in refrigerator for an hour.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Tear cake into chunks and arrange in glass bowl.
Slice bananas (round way).
Add pineapple.
Prepare instant pudding mix according to directions on package.
Pour over fruit and cake. Let set in refrigerator for about 2 hours.
Then top with Cool Whip and cherry pie filling and refrigerate.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix and stir to dissolve sugar and pineapple juice.
Add 1/2 gallon of ice cream and lemonade.
Stir in ice cream until dissolved.
Add 4 bottles of ale.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, water chestnuts, almonds and chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Combine next 4 ingredients, mixing well. Spoon mixture over chicken and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Yield: 6 servings.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix together 7 cups of water and 2 cups of sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Boil 2 cups water (separate from first mixture) and add the tea bags.
Remove from heat and let steep 15 minutes.
Let everything cool.
Add orange juice, lemonade and brandy.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze in an oblong cake pan.
To serve, mix half and half with 7-Up for a glass or in punch bowl.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Do not overbeat. Spoon batter into 12 (2 1/2-inch) greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut and ginger rice
directions: Bring water, coconut milk and ginger to boil. Add rice. Cover. Reduce heat to low. Cook for about 20 to 25 minutes. Turn off heat and let stand with lid on for 8 to 10 minutes longer. Serves 2 to 4.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup poppy seed with the warm water and let it set for a little while.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hayden salad
directions: Grind all
of
the
first
ingredients.
Cover
with canning salt and let stand for 2 hours. Squeeze out salt.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for
about
40 to 45 minutes or until thick enough to can.
Pack
into jars and seal.
Process according to recommendations.

title: french silk pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg.
(This is very important to the texture of the pie.)
Pour into baked pie shell and chill until firm.
Top with whipping cream.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate.

title: mallow-nut fudge
directions: In large bowl, combine marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts. In large pan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to boil. Cook and stir over medium heat to 236° on candy thermometer (soft ball stage).
Add vanilla.
Pour over marshmallow mixture.
Beat well until they melt.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Cool; cut into squares.

title: beefy macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Drain grease.
Cook elbow macaroni until tender, but still firm.
Drain.
Add to macaroni and beef mixture catsup, seasoned salt and Parmesan cheese.
Cook on low heat about 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: blender pumpkin pie(no crust)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend at high speed for 10 to 15 seconds.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet cabbage slaw
directions: Mix the first five ingredients. Add the salad dressing of mayonnaise as needed for the consistency you desire. It is better if refrigerated for at least one hour before serving.

title: stir-fry lemon chicken
directions: In a small bowl, stir together cornstarch, salt and thyme. Stir in lemon juice and water until smooth. Set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount of grease. Combine all ingredients and pour into baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, celery and onion for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add chicken soup, water and rice; boil for 10 minutes.
Mix in cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits; add to juice 1 box of lemon instant pudding, then add and fold in the fruit.
You may add any or all of the following:
cherries, pecans or coconut.

title: artichoke chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, melt 4 tablespoons butter or margarine and brown seasoned chicken.
Place chicken in large casserole.
In another skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute mushrooms for 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and stir in bouillon and sherry.
Cook 5 minutes and arrange artichokes between chicken in casserole.
Pour mushroom mixture over all and bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Baste while cooking for moistness.

title: banana nut cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt with a wire whisk.
Blend sugars in electric mixer; add butter and mix to a grainy paste.
Add egg, flavoring and banana; beat until smooth.
Add the flour mixture, 1 cup chocolate chips and the walnuts; blend at low speed until just combined.

title: ham ball
directions: Let cream cheese reach room tempeature.
Add other ingredients.
Chop ham and mix all together.
Form a ball and serve with crackers.
(I mix mine in the food processor.)

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Dissolve jello with water.
Add pop; set aside.
Bake cake according to box instructions; cool 10 minutes.
Pour jello mixture over cake after punching holes in cake.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make topping for cake.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Put 1/2 mixture in 10 x 13-inch cake pan and set in refrigerator.
Spread sour cream on top when jelled, then put remainder of jello on top.

title: alabama slammer
directions: Mix in glass over ice.

title: virgin mary
directions: Start with Hunt's tomato juice.
Mix the remaining ingredients into the tomato juice.

title: clam balls
directions: Prepare bread in large crumbs.
Melt butter and add pepper, salt, Worcestershire sauce.
Mix bread, onion, parsley and clams. Add melted butter mixture and shape into balls.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Cut in the shortening with a pastry cutter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Reserve 1 cup of this crumb mixture for the topping. Dissolve the baking soda in the buttermilk. Add this to crumb mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in the chopped nuts and the raisins.
Pour the batter into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Sprinkle with the leftover crumb mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until the cake tester emerges clean.
Good appetite!

title: turkey macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in a large pan of boiling water as label directs or until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain well.
In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, onions, salt and pepper. Gently stir in macaroni, turkey, grapes and celery.
Cover and chill until serving time.
To serve, spoon salad onto dish lined with salad greens.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate pecan thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix sugar, margarine, mint leaves and egg in large bowl. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.

title: herb baked chicken
directions: Combine garlic salt, paprika, oregano and pepper.
Rub over chicken.
Arrange chicken in a 12 x 8-inch dish with meatier portions toward edge of dish.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High power for 10 1/2 to 12 minutes. Chicken should be tender.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel rolls
directions: The night before:
Butter a large Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecans in pan.
Put frozen rolls in pan.
May cut in halves if you wish. Sprinkle pudding.
Pour melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon over the top.
Let set on countertop over night, uncovered.
Next morning:
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert on plate. Perfect for holiday mornings.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil fryer.
Debone and cut in bite-size pieces.
Soak bread in broth of chicken (2 to 2 1/2 cups).
Saute celery, bell pepper and onion in butter.
Combine all and put in casserole dish and bake like regular dressing.
Cook at 400°.

title: homemade cocoa mix
directions: Mix well and put in airtight can.
Use 4 tablespoons in a cup of water.

title: hot cheese puffs("a favorite from the '76 cookbook".)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in baking powder, salt and paprika.
Fold in cheese.
Spread 1/4-inch thick on Toast Beds. Broil until browned.
Serve immediately.
Broil about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cream in butter.
Add beaten egg yolks and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cumin turkey tenderloins
directions: In food processor, fitted with metal blade, process cilantro, onion, juice, cumin, salt and pepper until smooth.

title: mexican wedding bells
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy. Stir in flour until well blended.
Add nuts.
Chill 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° until light golden, 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove to rack (close to each other).
While still warm, sift heavily with confectioners sugar.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Cream dressing, cocoa and sugar.
Sift flour and soda.
Mix all with vanilla and water.
Pour into two 8-inch pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with white frosting or dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Roll meat, cheese and onion into tortillas softened in hot grease.
Place each enchilada in greased, oblong pan.
Cover with chili (spreads easier when heated).
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and enchiladas are hot.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a one-quart casserole dish.
In one-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook chopped onions until tender.
Stir in soup and cream cheese cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and hot.
In casserole dish, alternatively layer frozen potatoes and hot cream sauce, ending with a sauce layer.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn bread squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and green pepper together; drain and add all other ingredients except bread crumbs. Put half of bread crumbs in bottom of greased casserole dish. Pour on squash mixture. Cover with remaining bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Dice entire stalk of celery and the onion.
Brown meat in small amount of Crisco.
Add celery and onions to meat and bake in oven until the meat is tender.
When meat is done, remove from pan and let cool.
While meat cools, make brown gravy from meat drippings. Use the same pan you cooked the meat in.
Add all of the seasoning packages, salt, Accent and pepper.
Pour excess water from the vegetables and bean sprouts and then add to gravy.
Cut meat into small pieces and add it to vegetables and gravy mixture.
Cover and heat slowly until heated through.
Serve over cooked rice or the canned chow mein noodles.
Set out the soy sauce to be used as desired.

title: summer pudding
directions: Line 1-quart bowl with bread, trimming to fit.
Combine berries and sugar in medium saucepan.
Heat, stirring over medium heat, just until sugar is dissolved and berries release their juice, about 4 minutes.
Pour fruit and juice into bread-lined bowl.
Top with a layer of bread and cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Place on a plate and cover with saucer that fits just inside bowl. Weight down with 2-pound can.
Refrigerate overnight.
To serve, remove can, saucer and plastic wrap.
Run knife around edge of bowl to loosen pudding.
Invert onto plate.
Serve with a topping of yogurt.

title: adventure sandwiches
directions: Trim crusts and cut in fancy shapes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and cornmeal.
Pour 1/2 into each unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° until done.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: shrimp chefs salad
directions: Put the chilled greens in a bowl.
If the shrimp are small, leave them whole.
If medium, slice through the center lengthwise. If large, slice them through the center and then cut across, making each shrimp into four pieces.
Place on top of greens; sprinkle with capers.
Pour over the dressing, to which you have added a little curry powder, if you wish.

title: pizza bread
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and sugar.
Combine flour in bowl with salt and 1 1/4 cups warm water, oil and yeast mixture.
Knead until soft and satiny, adding more flour, if needed.
Let rise 3/4 hour.
Punch down and fit into pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Brush with oil.
Make indentations and insert rosemary and garlic.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Cut and serve while hot. Serves 8 to 10.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in heavy saucepan over low heat. Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and half and half. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Add cheese and herbs, stirring until cheese melts. Layer half each of egg slices, parsley, bacon and cheese sauce in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Repeat layers of ingredients. Combine bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted butter. Sprinkle over casserole. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: tuna noodle salad
directions: In large bowl, put in noodles, tuna, eggs, celery, onions and olives.

title: aunt ruby's pecan pie
directions: Pour pecans in bottom of crusts.
Mix flour, sugar and salt. Add Karo, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and pour over pecans.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Check and if shakes, cook for additional 5 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Use an 11 1/2 x 16-inch greased pan or use a 9 x 13-inch pan for thicker cake.
Bake cake the day before.

title: swedish yeast coffee cake
directions: Bring milk, sugar, salt and oleo to scalding, then stir well. Place yeast in 1/4 cup water, until it rises up.
Add flour and cardamon seed (crushed) to the yeast and all the other ingredients.
Knead the dough, then let it raise double.
Roll out to a rectangle size.
Spread 1/2 stick oleo over all; sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll it up; cut it in two and place in 2 loaf pans.
Let raise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until done.

title: no cook pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks.

title: red leaf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl except Chinese noodles.
Add noodles upon serving. Serve chilled.

title: almond shortbread
directions: Beat the margarine, sugar, eggs and extract together until creamy. Add the flour and mix well. Divide dough in half and put in 2 (8-inch) cake or pie tins. Brush with the egg white and sprinkle with sugar and sliced almonds. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Blend together flour and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Roll dough into balls (using teaspoon ball).
Beat egg whites separately; with fork, dip balls into egg whites.
Roll into nuts.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased pan; press thumbprint in and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix no bean chili and Philadelphia cream cheese.
Heat in microwave.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: plantation chicken
directions: Boil chicken and reserve broth. Chop onions, bell pepper and celery; saute in margarine. Add chicken, soup, milk and 1 1/2 cups chicken broth; stir until smooth. Take off heat and add eggs and bread crumbs. Pour into a large greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with grated cheese and let melt when ready to serve.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except grape leaves. Wash leaves; remove stems. Put 1/4 to 1/2 cup mixture in each leaf and roll, tucking in ends. Place in one layer in shallow baking dish; pour in small amount of water or chicken broth to prevent sticking. Cover and simmer in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or room temperature.

title: boiled spinach with sesame dressing(very popular dish)
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly; boil in a potful of water with stalks at bottom and leafy parts at top until soft.
Drain and rinse well.
Trim off spinach ends and squeeze out water.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch lengths.

title: shrimp destine
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add shrimp, lemon juice, wine, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Stir in dill weed and parsley.
Spoon over toasted rolls.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, eggs, onion and green pepper.
Salt and pepper well and shape into the form of an egg roll.
Stir in cornmeal, drop in frying pan with heated oil and brown on both sides.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 layers; slice into 4 layers.
Mix Crisco and sugar.
In saucepan combine milk, flour and butter; make a gravy, then cool.
Add cooled mixture to Crisco/sugar. Beat until smooth.
Smooth between layers and ice with chocolate frosting.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet-and-sour pork
directions: Combine 1/4 cup chicken broth, egg, cornstarch, flour and salt in a medium bowl; beat with a wire whisk until smooth.
Dip pork cubes into batter.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray. Place over medium heat until hot.
Add pork and cook 5 minutes or until browned.
Remove pork; drain on paper towels.
Keep warm. Wipe skillet with a paper towel and coat with cooking spray.
Add green pepper, carrot and garlic; saute until tender.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups chicken broth, red wine vinegar and soy sauce.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir into vegetable mixture and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes or until vegetable mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in pork cubes and sugar substitute.
Cover and simmer until pork is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: layered pudding dessert
directions: Combine and press into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
(It looks flaky and the edges pull away slightly when done.)
Only press into the bottom of pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 small loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape or put in loaf pan.
Bake about 1/2 hour at 350° until light brown on top.

title: meat boats
directions: Cut slice from top of rolls and hollow out the center of each. Reserve crumbs for meat mixture.
Season softened butter with garlic salt and spread on inside of rolls.
Saute onion and pepper in 1 tablespoons butter.
Soften bread crumbs in tomato soup and egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill rolls with mixture.
Place on a shallow pan (use nonstick spray) and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Can be made in advance and frozen.

title: tropical holiday salad
directions: Arrange all ingredients in large bowl.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spicy oven "fried" potato wedges(low fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray nonstick baking sheet with cooking spray.
Arrange potatoes on sheet and drizzle with oil. Turn potatoes, coating well with oil.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Peel and cut into halves. Sprinkle with salt.
In a skillet, mix sugar, oleo and water. Bring to a boil.
Put potatoes in syrup and cook over low heat turning occasionally until potatoes are candied, about 15 minutes.

title: beans for a crowd
directions: Fry bacon, crumble and drain half the grease from the pan. Chop onion and brown with the beef.
Drain completely.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 4 hours.

title: martha washingtons
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, coconut and powdered sugar.
Melt butter and pour over nuts.
Mix with first batch.
(To hand-mix, spray hands with Pam.)
Chill for 2 hours.

title: blender coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients into blender one at a time, blend after each one.
When finished pour mixture into 10 inch pie plate. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn oven to 350° bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bill's pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain; immediately return to pan.
Add olive oil; toss to coat.
Add milk, Parmesan cheese, onion, basil, lemon, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly, stirring constantly. Season.
Top with additional Parmesan cheese, basil and lemon slices.

title: ricotta and spinach quiche
directions: Thaw and cook spinach a few minutes. Squeeze out water and combine with Ricotta cheese, a pinch of nutmeg and 1/2 cup Parmesan. Spread over 2 cooked deep-dish pie crusts. Beat eggs lightly. Combine with milk and cream and season with salt and pepper. Pour egg and cream mixture over Ricotta and spinach mixture and sprinkle remaining Parmesan over top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Best quiche recipe I have ever tried.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Stir together 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.
Do not refrigerate.
Leave in bowl on counter and stir every day with wooden spoon for 6 days.
On day 10, add 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk and blend well.
Divide into 1 cup containers.

title: pralines a l'orleans
directions: Mix whipping cream and brown sugar together in a 4 qt microwave safe dish.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place all ingredients in crock pot.
Cook until heated through.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Blanch walnut halves for 30 seconds. Drain.
While still slightly damp, dredge nuts in sugar.
Spread them out to dry. Heat oil in wok to about 200° or until a test walnut browns in about 30 seconds.
If walnut is too dark, oil is too hot. Deep-fry nuts, 1/2 cup at a time. Sugar will melt and form a thin, hard outer shell.
Cool and cover until ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, bring 1/2 cup water to boiling.
Add broccoli and onion. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes (do not drain). Stir in soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Cook and stir about 4 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with croutons.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli for 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Arrange broccoli evenly on the bottom of the 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine chicken, soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over the broccoli in the baking dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over the mixture (additional cheese may be used, to taste).
Mix melted butter with cracker crumbs and sprinkle over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly, to avoid sticking. Add chocolate chips, stirring until chocolate is fully dissolved.
Add Marshmallow Creme.
Stir
until dissolved and it is smooth.
Add vanilla, nuts and peanut butter.
Mix evenly. Pour into slightly buttered pan.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: maple walnuts
directions: Cook syrup, cinnamon, butter and salt in an iron skillet until syrup loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Stir until nuts are coated.
Pour out onto wax paper.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In a medium Dutch oven, brown meat in small amount of oil and when almost brown add onion and saute until onion is golden.
Add wine, beef broth and seasonings.
Simmer very slowly (2 1/2 hours) with cover on.
Add mushrooms and thicken with water and flour. Serve over buttered noodles.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onions in shortening.
Add other ingredient and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour mixture into baking dish and cover with cornbread batter.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Blend flour, soda and salt.
Mix into sugar/shortening mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Place cauliflower, chicken broth and bouillon in large pan. Bring to boil and cook until cauliflower is tender.
Strain and save broth.
Melt butter in pan.
Add flour; mix well.
Add to cauliflower.
Stir, then add broth, half and half and cheese. Stir until melted.
It sticks easily, so stir.
